title: pineapple tea sandwiches
directions: Mix well. Spread on trimmed sandwich bread quarters.

title: one dish meal
directions: Cook meat, salt, onion and pepper until meat is brown.
Cook macaroni until almost tender (about 5 minutes).
Mix all ingredients in casserole and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin butterscotch cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a large mixer bowl, beat pumpkin, eggs, sugar and oil at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in dry ingredients just until blended.
Stir in 1 cup of walnuts.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch morsels and remaining nuts.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Drain and crumble. Add onion to bacon drippings and cook until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add seasonings and broth.
Bring to a boil and add potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Remove bay leaf. Serve while hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked beans and bacon
directions: Drain your pork and beans.
Put a layer of beans and a few slices of bacon and sprinkle brown sugar.
Add catsup and mustard to taste.
Just continue to layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juices
from fruit and mix with pudding and Tang. Mix well and pour over fruits.	Use any other fruits with this or substitute to your own taste.
Great dessert for someone on a diet.

title: juice punch
directions: Cook Stirring often until mixture thickens and boils.
Cover and continue cooking over low heat for 20 minutes.
Pour into a loaf pan and cool.
Slice and Fry.
Serve with Syrup.
Very Good.

title: yam casserole
directions: Bake at 350° until firm.

title: cheese straws
directions: Warm cheese and butter. Mix well. Add dry ingredients. Put in cookie press to form small strips. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until puffed.

title: oyster dressing
directions: In heavy skillet, saute seasonings until transparent.
Add bread that has been soaked in oyster water and squeezed out and chopped.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Add oysters, thyme, bay leaves, salt, pepper and cayenne to taste.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature and add 2 beaten eggs.
Should dressing be too wet, add a little bread crumbs.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry until golden brown. Place in a greased casserole dish and add 1 can of mushrooms plus 2 cans of either beef broth or beef consomm.

title: mary's apple brownies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Beat in eggs and oil.
Add apple and nuts and blend well.
Pour into a
lightly oiled and floured baking pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: crab and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain. Heat soup, stirring until smooth.
Add butter and milk.
When hot, remove from heat and stir in grated cheese, saving some to sprinkle on top.
Combine cheese sauce with spaghetti, crab meat and pepper.
Place in greased, shallow casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for about 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Add nutmeg, allspice, cloves and vanilla.
Mix and add strawberry jam.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan or 2 regular pans. Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: bob's blueberry sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, blueberries and lemon juice.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Add and cook until thickened.
Chill before topping cheese cake.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl place beef, bread crumbs, onions, egg, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Mix with hand until well combined.
In 9-inch pan, press meat mixture over bottom and sides to rim, forming a shell.
Bake until meat is firm, 15 minutes.
Remove excess fat and set aside.
In medium bowl stir together potatoes, cheese wedges, peas and carrots.
Spoon into meat shell.
Bake until heated thoroughly and cheese melts, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oven rice
directions: Cook meat until pink. Add other ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry hamburger until it loses its color.
In saucepan, combine all ingredients and simmer several hours.
This makes enough sauce for about 3/4 pound spaghetti.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Beat lemonade in large bowl.
Gradually spoon in ice cream, blending well.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth. Freeze, if necessary, until mixture will mound.

title: large pigs in blanket
directions: Cut each biscuit in half.
Wrap biscuit around hot dog.
Bake according to biscuit directions, usually 450° for 8 minutes. These are great for a kids party or something different for lunch!

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Bake in 2 cake pans or a sheet pan.
You don't want the cake very thick.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour pineapple juice over cake. Spread pineapple over cake.
Mix softened cream cheese, instant pudding and milk.
Spread over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over cream cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: quick hot open face tuna sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on 6 slices of bread or 6 pieces of bun.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Could top each sandwich with cheese of choice.

title: apple mince pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Combine sugar with flour; sprinkle about 3 tablespoons over shell.
Place sliced apples in layers in shell, sprinkling each layer with sugar-flour mixture (reserve 3 tablespoons).
Spread top with mincemeat, reserving 1/2 cup. Arrange apple rings on top.
Fill apple centers with remaining mincemeat.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar-flour mixture; dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 425° for about 40 minutes, until apples are tender.
Makes 10 servings.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Set in refrigerator until congealed. Add well drained pineapple, whipped cream (or Cool Whip).
Break 1/2 cake into small chunks; place in large pan.
Pour gelatin mixture over.
Break remaining cake pieces and put over gelatin mixture.
Cover with Dream Whip (or Cool Whip) and coconut.
Serves 15 or more.

title: cabbage and corn dish
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Add water and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add shredded cabbage and corn.
Cook 7 minutes in covered pan; add bacon and serve.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; beat egg, milk,
vanilla and butter and add to dry.
Top with 1/3 cup powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and 4 teaspoons melted butter.
Melt butter; mix rest of ingredients and spread over cake.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: homemade rotel
directions: Cook mixture until onions and peppers are tender.
Place in hot jars while hot; this will seal jars.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Combine oil, garlic and onion in skillet.
Add bouillon cubes. Add clams.
Mix together in cup, water and starch and slowly add to skillet, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Pour over cooked linguini.

title: robert redford cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix by hand until it is a crumb mixture. Press into a 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake for 15-20 minutes.
Cool.

title: tantalizing toffee
directions: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups of the walnuts for toffee.
Finely chop remaining 3/4 cup walnuts for topping.
In a 2-quart glass measuring cup with a handle, combine sugar, water, corn syrup and butter.
Microwave at High 5 minutes.
Stir well until sugar dissolves.	Microwave at High 16 to 20 minutes or until mixture reaches 300°.
Stir in the coarsely chopped walnuts and quickly spread in a buttered 15 x 10 cookie sheet.	Let stand until cooled completely.
Place chocolate in a 3-cup glass measuring cup. Microwave at High 30 seconds; stir to melt completely.
Spread the chocolate over the cooled toffee.
Sprinkle finely chopped walnuts evenly over the chocolate.	Let stand several hours until chocolate is set, then break into pieces.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend with a beater the sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to the pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Do not overbeat; this is a quick bread, doing so will cause the bread to be tough.
Add nuts and pie filling; blend well.
Generously coat loaf pans with cooking oil. Pour mixture into prepared pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: date filled drop cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in warm water.

title: golden lemon cheese pie
directions: In mixer, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Top with Golden Lemon Topping and chill for at least 3 hours.

title: layered lettuce(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix mayonnaise, salad oil and sugar.
Gently spread over layered ingredients.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and bacon on top.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and set aside. Mix rhubarb and 1/2 cup sugar. Combine and set aside. Cream butter, egg, sugar and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients. Add alternately with 1 cup buttermilk. Fold rhubarb mix into cake.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Cook noodles.
In greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish, make layers of noodles, spaghetti sauce and oregano, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat until all is used.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saut the first 5 ingredients together in a large pan, then cover with a lid for later. Mix together rest of ingredients. When the rice mixture has browned, pour in the tomato sauce mixture and bring to a boil. Turn heat to low. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with cheese and herbs
directions: Pound chicken breasts into cutlets, 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Beat butter until fluffy; stir in oregano, marjoram and parsley.
Cut cheese lengthwise into 8 pieces. Spread half of the herb butter on cheese.
Place piece of cheese on each cutlet and roll up, jelly roll fashion, tucking ends in to seal tightly.
Coat rolls with flour.
Dip in egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage; pour off fat.
Add celery and cook 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except peppers.
Simmer 30 minutes, covered.
Add peppers.
Cook 15 minutes more.

title: grilled catfish with salsa
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over fillets.
Marinate at least 15 minutes.
Brush grill with salad oil and grill catfish over medium-hot coals for 7 to 8 minutes per side.
Spoon salsa over fish and serve.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook and drain limas.
Saute onions and pepper in butter.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese and crackers.
Put in greased baking dish.
Top with cheese and crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Pour cherries in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart deep dish casserole dish. In medium-size mixing bowl, beat shortening, sugar and egg together.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to the wet ingredients.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tutti frutti ice cream
directions: Process fruit in food processor until well blended; set aside. Beat eggs.
Add salt, sugar and vanilla, mixing well.
Beat in canned milks.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into freezer can.
Finish filling with regular milk.
Freeze according to freezer directions.
Enjoy.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; cool.
Combine cake mix, eggs, gelatin, flour and cooking oil.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans for 20 minutes at 350° or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Use canned icing.

title: sweet-n-sour dip
directions: Bring to boil and serve.

title: jiffy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix the ingredients in a blender until well blended.
Bake over chicken, pork chops or ribs.

title: to die for dessert
directions: Line pan with ice cream sandwiches.
Add caramel and chocolate syrup.
Add Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Crumble Heath bar on top.
Freeze.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix all together the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg according to directions.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Grease 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet and place wax paper over pan leaving a couple inches wax paper hang over each end.
Then grease over top of wax paper.
Mix ingredients.
Pour into pan and spread evenly and smoothly in a thin layer.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Will burn easily, watch closely.

title: french toast
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Blend well with a wire whip.
Add vanilla, sugar and dash of cinnamon to taste. Blend well.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate prior to serving.

title: hershey-peanut blossoms
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream Crisco, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°;
remove and press Kisses in middle; return to oven.
Bake 2 to 5 more minutes.
Cool.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix flour, salt and cheese together.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce, mustard and margarine.
Knead all to form a soft ball.
Pinch off ball and make small balls on ungreased pan. You can mash down with a fork or place a 1/2 pecan on top of ball. Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: hot turkey sandwiches
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in roaster.
Cover with cheese.
Cover and heat at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Spread on buns or over biscuits.

title: texas fajita chile
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and bell pepper in oil for 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in kidney beans, shredded meat, tomatoes, Skillet Sauce, corn, tomato juice and chili powder. Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: dream pudding torte(sugar free)
directions: Mix well. Pat into 9 x 13 pan. Mix 1 large box sugar free butterscotch pudding as directed on pkg, pour over crumbs. Mix: 1 large pkg sugar free chocolate pudding as directed on box, pour over first pudding. Spoon
on 9 oz. Cool whip. You may sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs for garnish.

title: raspberry chicken
directions: Melt the butter in large skillet and saute the chicken until lightly browned on each side and cooked throughout.
Remove the chicken to a platter and keep warm.
Add the remaining ingredients to the skillet and cook on a high heat until the sauce thickens slightly.
Pour the sauce over the warm chicken and serve immediately.
Serves 4.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Cooking time:
25 minutes.

title: easy dessert
directions: Tear up angel food cake.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Make chocolate pudding according to directions on box.
Pour over angel food cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apple delight
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place apples in the pan and sprinkle with dry gelatin.
Mix margarine, flour and sugar until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned scalloped potatoes
directions: In 2 quart saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended; continue cooking 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in milk and cook until sauce is thickened and smooth stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and set aside; stirring occasionally to keep skin from forming on sauce surface.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with onion in large skillet.
Drain excess fat. Add all other ingredients and simmer covered for 20 to 25 minutes. May need to add a little water, if needed.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Mix the first 5 together and make into patties.
Brown in oil on both sides.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour gravy over top of patties and place onion rings on top.
Simmer in oven for about 35 minutes.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, butter, sugar and baking powder into crumbs (use hands).
Take out 1/2 cup for top of cake.
Break eggs into bowl and add milk. Flavor with vanilla. Beat very hard. (Use wooden spoon.)
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle crumbs on top. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat eggs with an electric mixer on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in granulated sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.

title: taco casserole
directions: Follow directions on back of seasoning mix.
Mix with hamburger that has been browned.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with onions, lettuce, tomatoes and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with crushed Doritos.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine and blend in flour.
Chill for 1 hour or longer.
Shape into 1 inch balls and press into ungreased tart pans.

title: orange whip
directions: Combine juice, milk, water, sugar and vanilla in blender. Blend on high speed.
Add crushed ice and blend.
Makes 4 to 6 glasses.

title: miracle meat rolls
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, egg and salt; mix well.
Pat meat mixture into 14 x 8-inch rectangle on foil or waxed paper.
Combine potatoes, eggs, salad dressing, cheese, celery and onion.
Mix lightly; season to taste.
Spread potato mixture over meat.
Roll up jelly roll fashion, beginning at narrow end.
Chill several hours; slice meat roll into 6 servings.
Bake on rack of broiler pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chicken with 2 tablespoons grated cheese.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk and 1/4 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts (low heat).

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix flour, butter and whipping cream.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll about 1/3 of the dough at a time, 1/8-inch thick, on floured cloth covered board.
(Keep remaining dough refrigerated until ready to roll.)
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Transfer rounds with metal spatula to piece of waxed paper that is heavily covered with sugar.
Turn to coat each round.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick each round with fork 4 times.
Bake just until set, but not brown, 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool.
Just before serving, put cookies together in pairs with a Creamy Filling.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix egg and potatoes together; use enough flour to bind mixture together.
Melt a little fat in frypan, when hot put 3 to 4 large spoonfuls of mixture in pan.
After a few minutes, turn. Press down slightly.
Will slice and cook other side.
Cook until both sides are golden brown.
Serve hot, with steaks, mixed grills, eggs and bacon or with hamburgers.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey; heat soups in a saucepan and add browned meat.
Line a casserole dish with plenty of chips; pour soup/meat mixture over them.
Crumble chips over the top.
Heat thoroughly at 350° for 30 minutes.
Delicious!

title: fluffy orange dessert(reduced calories)
directions: Pour can of pineapple (juice and all) into large bowl.
Mix in dry Jell-O mix.
Fold in Cool Whip and other ingredients being used.
Pile into pretty dessert bowl and chill well.

title: carrot apple muffin
directions: Mix apples, carrots and sugar together.
Set aside.
In large bowl mix dry ingredients, stir well.
Combine with apple mixture, mix in walnuts.
Add eggs and vegetable oil.
Stir until just combined.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, lemon juice, salt, mayonnaise, Accent, celery, eggs, soup and onion and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with cheese
and	crushed
potato
chips.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.	Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put 1 cup of brown sugar and water in medium saucepan.
Heat until it gets slightly thick, then add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and A.1. sauce.
Store in refrigerator for later use.
Keeps for about 2 months.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; combine broccoli and all remaining ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; top with cheese and sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: club crackers
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on Club crackers.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Break apart when cooled. Should make 1 box of crackers.
These are scrumptious and great to take to a party.

title: green peppers stuffed with mashed potato salad
directions: Prepare Potato Buds as directed on package for 4 servings. Stir in eggs, pickle relish, onion, pimiento and vinegar; chill.

title: country favorite pork(created by jeff galle)
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over pork.
May use pork chops, pork steak or pork ribs.
Especially good with boneless butterfly pork chops.
Cover (be sure and don't use aluminum foil) and place in refrigerator 24 to 48 hours.
Remove pork from marinade and grill as desired.
Then add more pork and return to the refrigerator for another great meal.

title: spread apple pie
directions: Cook until apples are done, but not dry.
If you have to, add water.
Take leftover homemade biscuits and slice in halves.
Put layer of biscuits and layer of apple mixture.
Repeat layer, ending with apples on top.
Make as many layers as you have apples and biscuits.

title: crumbled chicken casserole
directions: Blend melted butter and stuffing mix.
Line a greased 5 x 9-inch dish with half of crumb mixture.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over crumbs.
Top with other half of crumbs. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: In a double boiler, heat onion, milk and potatoes.
In a skillet, melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir to blend. Add this mixture to double boiler and cook over water for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn flake drops
directions: Bring sugar
and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Drop
on wax paper by teaspoon.

title: artichokes and lima beans in lemon-dill sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in pan. Add green onions and saut for 1 minute. Add lima beans and enough water to cover. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Add artichokes, dill and lemon. You may want to start with 1/2 the lemon juice and then adjust to taste at the end. Add enough water to barely cover again and simmer on low heat until vegetables are tender and sauce has reduced. For a thicker sauce, dissolve 1 to 2 teaspoons cornstarch in 2 tablespoons cold water and add at the end.

title: fruit punch
directions: Thaw juices.
Mix first 5 ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add ginger ale and 7-Up.
Fills large punch bowl.

title: ground beef cups with creamed potatoes
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, 1/2 cup milk, 1 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; mix well. Line ungreased muffin cups with meat mixture about 1/4-inch thick. Place potatoes and remaining milk in saucepan; cover and cook slowly until thick. Season with salt and pepper. Fill meat cups with potatoes; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Spray grocery bag with Pam cooking spray.
Dump popped corn in bag.
Put brown sugar, syrup and oleo in bowl.
Do not stir. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
When done, add soda and mix. Dump mixture into bag of corn.
Fold bag and shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out and shake.
Microwave again for 30 seconds.
Dump onto cookie sheets to cool.

title: marbled chocolate bars
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions. Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Combine drained pasta and vegetables with remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Makes about 8 side dish servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together ingredients and chill overnight or at least 6 hours.
Cut out middle of bread into bite sized pieces.
Place mixture in the cut out space.
Great for a summer party.

title: eggplant creole
directions: Cook eggplant, covered,
in a small amount of water 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain, dice or slice up cheese.
Add 2/3 package to macaroni.
Add all other ingredients except remaining cheese.
Put in baking dish.
Mix well.
Add remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese slightly browns.
Yum good!

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Beat on medium with mixer, 1 to 2 minutes.
Put half of the cake mix into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with chocolate morsels. Drizzle with condensed milk.
Sprinkle with remaining cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Butter both sides of bread.
Fry in skillet and brown on both sides.
Remove from skillet and eat.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt in a bowl. Stir in unbeaten egg whites and almond extract and mix well. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until edges are brown. Remove from cookie sheet at once. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: chili cheese bites
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking powder to eggs.
Add melted butter to flour mixture.
Add chiles, cottage cheese and cheese.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco shell
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Then add shortening and mix.
Add 1 cup hot water.
Mix and let stand 5 minutes.

title: hot navy bean salad
directions: Place onion in bottom of serving dish and add hot beans. Cover and let stand 5 minutes or so.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring to blend.
Canned beans may be used.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into cubes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients, except macaroni.
Cook macaroni and cool. Mix with other ingredients.

title: condensed milk
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth using either a whisk or blender.
Makes 1 quart.

title: top hat
directions: Take a Ritz cracker, put a marshmallow on top, and put a cherry on top of the marshmallow.
Bake until the marshmallow is light brown.
Bake at 350°.
(Kids will love it.)

title: gelatin cake
directions: Mix boiling water and gelatin.
Let gelatin cool slightly.
Mix in cake mix.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: easy german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cocoa in bowl.
Stir in milk, vanilla, beaten eggs and melted margarine.
Blend well.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Put into the pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set around edges of pies.
Cool on racks.

title: cornflake chicken
directions: Beat egg and milk together.
Dip chicken in egg mixture the roll in cornflakes.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake 20-25 minutes at 375 degrees or until juices run clear.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Add butter, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Cut artichoke hearts and stir in.
Place in 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole and top with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Now beat egg whites until soft peaks form and add sugar, two tablespoons at a time, until stiff peaks form and sugar is dissolved.
Fold in chips and nuts.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine sugar and oleo and beat well.
Add egg, cinnamon, nutmeg and beat well. Gradually add flour and buttermilk with soda dissolved in buttermilk and beat.
Then add jam and mix through batter well.
Grease pan.
Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes, then turn out on cake plate and finish cooling before icing.
Makes 2 layers or 1 oblong cake.
Ice with caramel icing.
This was my Mother's recipe.

title: tear-apart cake
directions: Tear apart angel food cake and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake.
Mix together strawberries and strawberry gel.
Put on top. Keep in refrigerator.

title: ratatouille
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch thick slices, then 1-inch cubes. Cut zucchini
in 1/4-inch slices.
Thickly slice onions and cut peppers into 1/4-inch strips.
Brown eggplant in oil in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender.

title: choice lasagna
directions: Brown meat; add garlic, one tablespoon parsley, basil, 1 teaspoon salt, tomatoes and tomato soup.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to instructions.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, 1 tablespoon parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Place layer of noodles in greased casserole; add layer of meat-tomato mixture, layer of cottage cheese mixture and sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Repeat layers; sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp; chill sauce thoroughly. Fill a large bowl with crushed ice and place a dish of sauce in center; arrange shrimp over ice.
Serve with picks for dipping shrimp into sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Spread Miracle Whip on top until it covers completely to seal the bowl, as thin as possible to cover.
Sprinkle 2 or 3 tablespoons of sugar on top of this.
Sprinkle package of Good Seasons Italian dressing on this and add 1/2 to 1 cup Colby cheese, grated.
Cover and let set at least 8 hours.

title: my best friend's easy enchiladas
directions: Cut up chicken breast into small pieces and drop into deep pan of boiling water.
Continue to boil until chicken floats to top of water.
Heat oven to 350°.
Remove chicken and place into medium size bowl.
Allow to cool and separate with fingers or 2 forks. Mix in carton of sour cream, half of picante sauce and half of cheese.
Spray large baking sheet with Pam or lightly butter. Arrange 3 to 4 tortillas on sheet and fill centers generously with filling mixture.
Fold sides to center and flip over so that seams are on bottom.
Now mix rest of cheese and 1/4 of picante sauce and spoon over top of enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes until cheese on top melts.
Remove from pan with a spatula.
Enjoy!

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add cheese, ketchup and other ingredients.
Blend well over low heat.
Spread on party rye slices.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
Add rest of ingredients except cheese and sour cream.
Simmer until mixed and hot, then add cheese.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Do not boil. Serves 8; 289 calories per serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla together. Sift dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture. Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Crisscross with fork 2 times. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly. Remove from pan.

title: favorite broccoli salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine broccoli, bacon, onion and cheese.
In another small bowl, combine sugar and vinegar, mix well.
All mayonnaise until desired consistency.
Then pour over salad and mix well.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and butter.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
Stir in pimiento, parsley and onion. Cover and chill.
Add a little milk, if necessary, to make of dipping consistency.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: biscotti
directions: Mix in order written.
Dough will be sticky.
Make 4 small loaves on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until loaves are tan.
Cut loaves on slant.
Put back into oven and bake until golden brown.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Add crumbs, nuts, chocolate chips and coconut.
Do not mix.
Pour milk over all. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Also butterscotch or peanut butter chips can be used for variety or even mix them. Also nuts may be left out if wanted.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes until tender. Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp and mash. Add mushroom soup, butter, salt and pepper. Whip until light and fluffy while gradually adding milk.
Pile back into potato shells. Sprinkle shredded cheese over tops. Return to hot oven (450°) for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Chop onion and pepper; saute.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Combine all ingredients.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix well and put in refrigerator.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix together first the sugar and flour; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: roman holiday
directions: Saute uncooked macaroni, onion and bell pepper in fat.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Drain.
In a greased baking dish, alternately layers of meat mixture, tomatoes, macaroni and cheese. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: little smokies
directions: Wrap each Little Smokie in 1/4 slice of bacon (seam side down). Place in baking dish in rows.
Spread brown sugar on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: ratatouille
directions: Prepare 5 cups cubed, pared eggplant by washing and paring it, then cutting into 1/2 inch cubes.
Prepare 2 cups zucchini by washing and cutting into 1/2 inch cubes also.
Do not pare zucchini.
Cook and stir all ingredients until heated through. Cover; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: quick candy
directions: Combine marshmallows, cereal and peanuts in bowl; mix well. Melt white chocolate in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over cereal mixture; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until cool.

title: split pea soup(low-fat, low calories)
directions: Combine dried split peas, water and bay leaf and lite salt in large kettle.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Stir and make sure peas do not stick.
Add more water if it becomes too dry.
Add carrots, celery, onion and herbs. Continue to simmer 30 minutes or more.
Overcooking does not hurt this soup, as long as it does not stick and scorch.
Just before serving, add vinegar or lemon juice and pepper.
Makes 12 cups. Calories 106.
Contains fat 1 g, fiber 5 g and sodium 91 mg.

title: chocolate almond zucchini bread
directions: Mix and sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Combine eggs, sugar and oil; mix well.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Add flour mixture; blend lightly.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together; form into log and chill.
Wrap in tinfoil.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve sliced on Ritz crackers.

title: lasagna
directions: Use a long glass pan.
Start with a layer of sauce, then layer of noodles, then all cheeses until all is used.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broiler chicken
directions: Cut chicken in half.
Melt butter.
Add garlic salt.
Add other ingredients. Coat
chicken with black pepper and seasoned salt or garlic powder.
Sear chicken on hot grill.
Baste with butter mixture.
Cook approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: "old fashioned spice cake with caramel frosting"
directions: Mix 1 1/3 cups milk and vinegar; reserve (rest of milk is for frosting).
Beat vinegar mixture and remaining ingredients in large bowl at slow speed, scraping bowl constantly for about 30 seconds.
Beat on high for 3 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with light coat of Mazola spray oil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Stir in the rest.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: lorelei's eggplant parmesan
directions: Cook tomatoes and tomato sauce with spices for 1/2 hour, then set aside.
Slice eggplant in 1/4-inch slices.
Dip each slice in slightly beaten eggs, then in bread crumbs.
Fry on each side until slightly brown.
Cover cookie sheet or small baking pan with sauce.
Put a layer of eggplant.
Top again with sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, then Mozzarella cheese and bake in 350° oven until cheese melts together.
Serves 4, approximately.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, sugar and eggs one at a time.
Add baking powder to flour, then add flour mixture alternating with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring and bake at 300 degrees for one and a half hours.
DO NOT PREHEAT OVEN.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, add sugar and eggs and beat well.
Add oil and beat well.
Mix flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Add pumpkin, water and nuts and blend well. Pour into well buttered pans.
Makes two large loaves or 3 smaller loaves.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken, shrimp and rice(from guyana)
directions: Place chicken, water, leeks, bay leaf, parsley, salt and peppercorns in large pot and bring to a boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and let cool.
Strain and reserve broth.
Remove skin from chicken and slice meat into strips.
Bring 3 cups of reserved broth to a boil.
Add rice and stir once with a fork.
Lower heat; cover and cook rice about 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Heat oil in a large, heavy casserole and saute onions and garlic until golden brown.
Add rice and cook until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Add chicken, shrimp, crabmeat, ham, coriander, cumin, chili powder, mace and about 1/4 cup broth and combine thoroughly. Cook over low heat about 10 minutes or until ingredients are heated through.
Stir frequently.
Stir in peanuts and serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry-filled cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter in a mixing bowl until soft and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla, then flour and pulverized nuts.
Roll into bite size balls.
Place on a greased baking sheet and make a cavity in each ball with forefinger.
Bake in 300° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and fill cavities with 1/2 teaspoon of jam.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt over hot water, cocoa and Crisco.
Beat eggs and sugar. Sift and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in chopped nuts.
Spread in greased pan (Pam).
Bake until firm at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: christy's texas salsa
directions: Throw everything into a blender and pulse a few times. Put in jars and get your favorite chips! Enjoy! Will keep in your refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Saute with ground beef. Generously grease a 10 x 14-inch baking dish.
Place a layer of corn tortillas on bottom.
Add a layer of meat mixture, then a layer of chili beans, undrained.
Follow with a generous layer of grated cheese, then a layer of sliced black olives.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Spread cream of chicken soup on top, then pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over, cutting tomatoes in small pieces.
Cover and bake at 350° until thoroughly heated, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off excess fat.
Put beef in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onion; drain off fat.
Add bacon, onion and remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir together well. Cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.

title: steamed apple-date pudding
directions: Peel and coarsely chop cooking apple.
Heavily grease deep 2 1/2-quart heat safe bowl.
Cut foil 1 inch larger than top of bowl to use as cover.
Grease 1 side of foil well; set aside.
In blender at medium speed, blend dates and cranberry juice cocktail until smooth; set aside.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat sugar and butter just until blended.
Increase speed to high and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and next 5 ingredients, and date mixture; beat at low speed until well blended.
Increase speed to medium and beat 1 minute, scraping bowl.
With rubber spatula gently fold in chopped apple and walnuts.
Spoon mixture into prepared bowl and cover with foil, greased side down, tie tightly with string.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine vinegar, water, spices and pepper flakes.
Bring to boiling, lower heat and simmer 1 minute.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello, using the hot and then the cold water.
Add other ingredients; refrigerate until set up.

title: avocado dip
directions: Combine and chill at least 30 minutes.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook crumbled sausage until brown; drain.
Mix sausage with all other ingredients and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy blueberry crisp
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Put blueberries in pan.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour sugar, milk, eggs, Bisquick and butter over the blueberries.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well and cook until transparent, then about 3 minutes more, stirring often.
Remove from stove.
Add butter and red and yellow coloring.
Let cool while slicing basket of cleaned strawberries.
Mix into cooled glaze mixture.
Pour into cooled pie shell and refrigerate.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Place meat in crock-pot.
Pour sauce mixture over meat.
Cover.
Cook on low, 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with rice.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips in oleo.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 325° in unbaked pie shell until set.

title: zucchini raisin nut bread
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in mixer.
Add zucchini and blend.
Mix together in bowl flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, raisins and nuts and add slowly to mixture in mixer. Bake in greased and floured pans at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.
Serve plain or with cream cheese.

title: spam or treet and veg-all goulash
directions: Cut Spam/Treet into ten slices, then cut in halves.
Then cut halves diagonally across to make triangles.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole and heat in 425° oven while preparing other ingredients. Cook noodles 5 minutes and drain.
Blend mixed vegetables, soup, milk and onion with noodles.
Line casserole dish with Spam/Treet, reserving
8 slices for top.
Then pour mixture over Spam, placing 8 slices on top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes. It's very good.

title: ham and broccoli royale
directions: Cook rice following label directions; spoon into a greased refrigerator-to-oven 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook broccoli following label directions; drain well.
Place in a single layer over the rice in baking dish.
Melt butter or margarine in large frying pan; measure out 2 tablespoons and sprinkle over bread crumbs in a small bowl; set aside.

title: banana pudding bahamas style
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until lightly golden on top.
Cool; cut into squares.
Place a dollop of whipped cream or topping on each individual serving.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: german baby pancake
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Sift flour; measure and sift again with salt.
Add flour and salt to eggs in 4 additions, beating after each until mixture is smooth.
Add milk in 2 additions, beating slightly after each.
Beat in the melted butter (lightly).
Butter bottom and sides of heavy 8 or 9-inch frypan or pie pan.
Fill with mixture and bake in a 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: freezer corn
directions: Put all together in skillet or pot and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool, then put in bags and freeze.
When ready to cook, place in pan with small amount of milk or butter or water. Salt to taste.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and Wesson oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add pumpkin and beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Before baking, let set 30 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a large pan or skillet, saute onion in butter.
Add salt, oregano, cream of mushroom soup and 2 cans of water.
Add broccoli; mix in Minute rice.
Blend together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Stir cake mix and cocoa; add remaining ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool and frost with favorite icing.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Mix butter until smooth.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Alternate mixing in the flour and sour cream.
Add flavorings and mix thoroughly.
By hand with wooden spoon, mix in the egg whites.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured large tube pan.
Put in cold oven and turn to 300°.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
and bone	chicken.
Cook	broccoli
according
to package directions.
In
casserole	dish,
place
broccoli and then chicken.
Cover with
cream of chicken soup, curry powder and mayonnaise (mixed together).
Top
with bread crumbs (5 to 6 slices) and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt overnight. Drain and let stand in cold water for 10 minutes.
Drain. Dissolve sugar in vinegar and boil for five minutes, add to onions and cucumbers.
Add remaining ingredients to boiling vinegar and let cook.
Bottle.

title: sliced cucumber with sour cream sauce
directions: Cover cucumbers with ice water; soak for 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Drain and cover with rest of ingredients, beaten together.
Chill until served.

title: okra succotash
directions: *Remove cayenne pepper before serving.

title: salad bongo bongo
directions: Let cheese reach room temperature.
Drain pineapple and mix with cheese.
Heat lemon juice and sugar together until dissolved. Now dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup boiling water and mix with lemon juice and sugar.
Bring this mixture to a boil.
Let cool and add whipped cream.
Fold this mixture into the cheese and pineapple and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 4.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook slowly until mixture attains the desired thickness.
If applesauce is made of very bland apples, add up to 1 tablespoon lemon juice to taste.
Yield:
1 to 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and make into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Press with fork and bake in 350° oven.

title: beef jerkies("very good")
directions: All ingredients depends on the amount of beef you are marinating.
Get round steak.
Freeze for about 1 hour; this will help
you cut very thin slices.
Marinate about 24 hours.
If you have dehydrator, put on the screens and cook about 36 hours. If you use a conventional oven, put on rack that fits over a pan and cook at 200° until thin strips are very dry.
Good for camping, ball games, etc.
Does not require refrigeration.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Melt bouillon cubes in small amount of water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: church window
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips over low heat in heavy pan. Cool. Add marshmallows and nuts.
Divide into two parts. Roll each part in coconut, forming into a log shape.
Refrigerate overnight. Slice horizontally.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, shape into balls.
Put on cookie sheet in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Keep warm

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Cut thin slice of round steak (boneless) in long strips and pound a little Adolph's meat tenderizer into it.
Cut up cooked bacon in small pieces; also chop onions in small pieces.
Put some bacon and onions on each piece of meat.
Salt and roll up; fasten with toothpicks.
Roll in flour and brown.
Then cover all roll-ups with hot water and let simmer until tender.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together crushed pretzels, 5 tablespoons sugar and butter (melted).
Pat in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°. Cream together 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip; spread over pretzel bottom.
Prepare package of strawberry Jell-O, using 1 3/4 cups boiling water.
Stir in one box of sliced strawberries.
Chill until thick; spread over cream cheese and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, milk and spices, along with eggs.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix over this, then sprinkle the nuts over the top.
Drizzle the melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until brown.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: lemon bars
directions: With electric mixer, mix margarine, flour and powdered sugar. Pat in bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: friendship cake
directions: Line baking dish with crushed Oreo cookies.
Cream the cream cheese and margarine.
Fold powdered sugar in Cool Whip.
Mix Cool Whip mixture with cream cheese mixture.
Spread over Oreo cookies. Whip instant pudding with milk for pudding.
Add vanilla.
Spread over second layer.
Save small amount of Cool Whip and spread over top.
Use Oreo cookie crumbs or chocolate shavings to sprinkle on top.

title: overnite casserole
directions: Mix milk and soup until blended in a 2-quart microwave bowl. Add all ingredients, cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 12 hours.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 15 to 17 minutes.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Let stand, uncovered, until cheese melts.

title: streusel apple pie
directions: Can substitute 1 can of canned apples for fresh apples.

title: baked tomato "sandwiches" with montrachet(yields 24 servings)
directions: Cut tomatoes into 48 (1/2-inch) slices; reserve.
Combine Montrachet and cream cheese.
Add cream, chives and basil.
Spread 2 tablespoons cheese mixture on 24 reserved tomato slices.
Top with remaining slices to make "sandwiches".
Dip sandwiches in eggs; coat with crumbs.
Cover.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until cheese is firm.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a large bowl, make a stiff batter of all ingredients. Grease another bowl.
Put dough in and turn over (oily side on top).
Cover and let stand overnight.
Do not refrigerate.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients, then add the rest and mix well with mixer.
Flour an 8 1/2 x 11-inch cake pan and pour in cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out of the center clean.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oleo, sugar and cocoa.
After well blended, add flour and nuts.
Bake in a loaf pan, well greased and floured, at 350°.
When almost done, remove and cover with marshmallows evenly.
Return to oven until marshmallows are melted and golden brown.
Cool.

title: calico salad
directions: Drain peas, beans and corn.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Better if prepared day before serving.

title: sweet and sour dill pickles
directions: Wash freshly picked cucumbers and cut in 1-inch chunks or quarters, enough to fill 4 sterilized quart jars.
To each jar add 3 or 4 slices onion , 2 pieces celery and 2 heads of dill. Dissolve sugar and salt in vinegar and water.
Bring to boil. Pour while still hot over cucumbers in each jar to cover; seal at once.
For best flavor, do not use for 30 days.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: yellow squash, zucchini and onions
directions: Arrange squash and zucchini in steamer over 3/4-inch boiling salted water; partially cover and steam for 12 minutes or until tender.
Melt butter and saute onions just until crisp-tender.
Do not brown.
Add squash and zucchini and toss with salt and pepper.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Barely cook broccoli.
Layer it in 12 x 8-inch dish.
Spread turkey on top.
Combine milk and soup and mix until smooth.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: german beef supper
directions: Brown beef in hot Crisco. Add apple, carrot, onion, water, wine, salt, garlic, bouillon, bay leaf and thyme. Combine cornstarch and cold water. Add to beef mixture. Cook and stir until thickened. Stir in Kitchen Bouquet. Serve over the egg noodles. Delicious served with a salad.

title: chicken ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans. Form into a ball. Refrigerate to chill. Roll in chopped pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; mix all ingredients except meat.
Mix well, then add ground chuck.
Mix well, then pour into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour, then top with ketchup and broil until brown.

title: pork chop and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown chops in a little butter.
Slice onion and add to chops after they are turned.
Remove to a greased casserole.
Slice cabbage thinly and pack tightly around chops, filling to top (it will shrink).
Pour milk over to barely cover.
Add seasoned salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve with baked potatoes, spooning milk mixture over the potatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in low oven at 350° for 50 minutes. Garnish with pecan halves before baking.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together.
Drain and add oleo, egg, salt, pepper, soup and bread crumbs.
Put in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: curried rice
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups of water and salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil and add rice.
Cover.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour 1/2 cup of water over raisins.
Let stand 1 minute.
Drain raisins; set aside.
Combine butter and curry powder.
Stir curry mixture, raisins and walnuts into rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: miniature ham sandwiches
directions: Slice dinner rolls in order to have top and bottom.
Combine butter, sugar, mustard, onion and poppy seed in bowl.
Heat in microwave for 1 minute.
Spread mixture on bottom half of bread. Top with ham and cheese; place top of bread and spread with remaining butter mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain and mix remaining ingredients, including all liquids.
Let simmer in a large pot until flavors blend together, about 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings (approximately 1 cup each).
Each serving equals 2 meats, 1 bread and 1/2 vegetable.

title: kitchen cupboard surprise
directions: Fix rice in pan according to box instructions.
In medium skillet, combine sausage, onion, pepper and corn.
Cook over low heat until onion is tender.
Add cooked rice.
Stir in pizza sauce. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on low heat for approximately 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 9.

title: dede's poppy seed cheese bread
directions: Slice French bread (but not all the way through).
Put Monterey Jack cheese slices between each piece of bread.
Melt butter and drizzle between and on top of bread slices.
Sprinkle with poppy seed between and on top of bread slices.
Wrap in tinfoil and bake for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: cherry holiday balls
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, nuts, dates, coconut, vanilla and salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and shape around cherries.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in the bottom of a pie pan. Add the Hormel Chili and top with cheddar cheese. Heat in microwave for 5 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus tuna-pecan salad with water chestnuts
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayo, tuna, pecans, celery, pepper and water chestnuts, mixing well to evenly distribute and coat with mayo.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
If salad is dry, add a bit more mayo.
Serve as a sandwich filling or as a salad on a bed of lettuce.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer on medium; heat for about 20 minutes, then use.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the soup mix, beaten eggs, catsup and warm water.
Add bread crumbs, meat and chopped eggs and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Add butter, sugar and marshmallows to potatoes while hot.
Mix well until marshmallows melt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover souffle with additional marshmallows and melt and brown in oven at 400°.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift flour, spices, soda and salt in mixing bowl.
Add oil nd half the milk; mix for one minute.
Add remaining milk with eggs. Beat for four minutes.
Add fig preserves, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Pour melted butter over cracker crumbs, saving 4 teaspoons to put on top of stuffed crabs.
Add mayonnaise and other seasoning, then mix in crabmeat with fork to keep from breaking up.
Fill 6 large backs (or use small baking cups) generously, then sprinkle with cracker crumbs, pouring remaining butter on top.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: glazed peanuts
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Boil, stirring constantly, until all liquids are gone.
Put on a flat pan and bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in a greased casserole and bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 40 minutes.
Check for doneness at 35 minutes as ovens vary.
Serves six amply.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks and whites separately.
Combine all ingredients except egg whites.
Fold egg whites in.
Bake slowly for 35 minutes at 350.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Cool in refrigerator.
Add drained chestnuts, artichokes and other ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise with liquid from artichokes, add to other and toss.
Chill, let stand at room temperature 1 hour before serving.

title: strawberry lemon tea
directions: Combine water, preserves, Nestea and lemon juice in 1-quart pitcher. Stir to dissolve. Strain, if desired. Garnish with strawberries or lemon slices. Yields 2 servings.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar and let set 10 minutes.
Mix milk, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add milk mixture to yeast mixture and add melted shortening.
Add flour and mix well, then let set for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna pie
directions: Cook spaghetti per package directions and drain.
Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" by lining a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: May use more salad dressing as desired.
Mix well.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Combine with cracker crumbs and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (I use glass).

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Add yeast and buttermilk to make soft dough.
This does not need to rise before baking.
Will keep in fridge up to 2 weeks.
Bake at 450°.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Brown bread crumbs, margarine and onions.
Heat tomatoes and sugar.
Put a layer of bread crumbs mix and layer tomatoes until all is used.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Saute ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble; drain off pan drippings.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onions and brown sugar.
Place each biscuit in a greased muffin cup, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon meat mixture into cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix together; top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off
fat.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer covered about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, and sugar.
Add milk, water, and cook until thick.
Stir constantly.
Stir in butter.
Delicious with biscuits.

title: mother's and ima's dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Be sure it is not dry.
Should be soupy. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400°
until set.
Serves 12.

title: caramel delight dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk. Refrigerate.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease 2 baking sheets (12 x 15 1/2-inch or larger).
Place sugar, corn syrup and water in a 3-quart ovenproof bowl.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.
When soft ball stage is reached, stirring occasionally, stir in peanuts (syrup forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water and flattens upon removal).
Cook on 80% power for 10 to 12 minutes until hard stage is reached (syrup separates into threads which are hard and brittle).
Stir in butter and baking soda.
Pour in pan.
Spread 1/4 inch thick.
Cool. Break into pieces.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Buy 1/2 pound of ham, sliced a little thicker.
Stack and chop finely.
Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Form into a ball and roll in nuts to coat.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 6.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet
potatoes in water to cover over until soft. Remove, cool and
peel skin off.
Slice in 1/4 inch slices and brown on each
side
in
butter or oil in frying pan at medium heat.
Drain
on
paper
towels
and sprinkle with sugar while still hot.
Makes approximately six servings.

title: broccoli-ham casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine in a Dutch oven until tender.
Add soup, cheese and garlic powder.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add mushrooms and next three ingredients.
Gently stir in pimientos.
Spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and chill in refrigerator 8 hours.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown the beef and onions. Add all the chopped vegetables and tomatoes; bring to a boil. Add the barley, water and all spices. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup. Mix syrup, egg, flour, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook until thickened.
Cool completely. Mix cooked macaroni, oranges, marshmallows and custard. Chill and add bananas when serving.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Put sour cream, cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla into large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in noodles and raisins.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn oven up to 400° and bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with some onion.
Slice a layer of potatoes into a good sized casserole, then a layer of carrots on the top of potatoes.
Then add the browned hamburger and onion.
Add another layer of potatoes.
Empty can of soup and milk; pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Shred shrimp.
Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with rye crackers.

title: barbecue sausage
directions: Mix ingredients together in crock-pot except sausage.
Add sausage links, cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Add enough water to cover sausage.
Cook on low heat for 4 to 5 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add mashed bananas, flour, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Pour dough in loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 1 hour at 300° until brown.
(This is the best I have ever had.)

title: corn meal biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add egg, milk and butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in cranberry
sauce.
Pour
into
9 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex baking pan. Chill until almost firm.

title: coke cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour; set aside.
Bring the next 3 ingredients to a boil and then let cool.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top cake with marshmallows after cake is done.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Ice cake while warm.

title: eight-layer salad
directions: Layer in a large salad bowl. (Can prepare enough of each ingredient to layer twice.)
Cover and place in refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: * Do not substitute.

title: baked squash
directions: Saute chopped onions.
Slice squash thin.
Combine all ingredients together, except bread crumbs.
Pour mixture into a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Boil together the milk, sugar, corn syrup and chocolate.
Stir as little as possible until it makes a ball when dropped in cold water.
Add the butter.
Cool the mixture and beat until thick. Add nuts and vanilla and turn out on buttered pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg, honey and flavoring thoroughly.
Blend flour, soda and salt; stir in.
Chill dough in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool, ice and decorate.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: creole cream cheese ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender or food processor. Pulse a few times to break up chunks of cream cheese. Pour into an ice cream freezer and process until frozen.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix and sift flour and salt.
Add cocoa and sift together twice.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Gradually add flour and cocoa mixture.
Add pecans.
Turn into greased shallow pan.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut into squares before removing from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Place in a cookie jar or covered dish immediately.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with brown sugar, butter slices, coconut (1 cup) and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add 1 cup miniature marshmallows to top and return to oven until marshmallows are melted and lightly browned.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, pepper, onions and celery; put in large pot with other ingredients.
Boil at least 1 1/2 hours.
Put in jars and seal.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine melted margarine and sugar.
Blend in crumbs.
Press evenly into pie pan.
Chill.
For a chocolate crust, chocolate cookie crumbs may be substituted for the graham cracker crumbs. Makes 1 pie shell.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° in a well-greased oblong dish for 45 minutes to 1 hour until gingerbread springs back at touch.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain peas and artichoke hearts.
Cut artichokes into quarters.
Marinate peas, artichoke hearts and celery in salad dressing overnight.
Before serving, add tomatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni sauce
directions: In a large pot, put 2 cans of tomato puree and a 1/2 can of water.
Keep the 1/4 cup puree for the meat balls.
Bring the puree to a boil and add the sugar.
(This cuts the acid in the tomatoes.) Now put the gas on simmer very low and add 1 or 2 tablespoons of basil.
Put a little oil in frypan to brown sausage.
Prick the sausage before you fry to release some of the fat in sausage.
Once brown, put in the pot of sauce.

title: grilled eggplant and tomato sandwiches
directions: Heat barbecue on medium-high heat.
Sprinkle eggplant slices generously with salt and let stand 5 minutes.
Pat dry.
Combine oil, garlic and chopped basil in small bowl; season with salt and pepper.
Brush eggplant slices, bread and tomato slices with garlic oil.
Grill eggplant until very tender and slightly charred, turning frequently, about 7 minutes per side.
Arrange bread and tomatoes on barbecue during last 3 minutes of eggplant-grilling time and cook until bread is golden and tomatoes begin to soften (less than 1 minute per side).
Transfer 2 slices of bread to a plate.
Top the remaining 2 slices with eggplant, cheese, tomato slices and whole basil leaves, divided evenly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover grill until cheese melts, about 1 minute. Transfer sandwiches to plates.
Top with second bread slices. Garnish with basil sprigs and serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: choco-mint snaps
directions: Melt chips
in
double boiler.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl
combine
shortening,
sugar
and
egg.
Beat until creamy. Mix
in
corn syrup, peppermint and melted chocolate. Blend in flour.
Shape
in balls using 1 tablespoon of dough. Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: low calorie hot dish
directions: Chop cabbage in pieces; place in bottom of greased baking dish. Brown meat and onion.
Pour off fat and stir in raw rice.
Put mixture on top of cabbage and cover with tomato juice or soup and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for at least 1 hour.
Watch that it doesn't get too dry.

title: "cream of" soup substitute
directions: Combine flour and water until smooth.
Heat evaporated skim milk in small saucepan.
Add flour and water.
Stir until thickened.
Add thickened mixture to recipe calling for condensed canned soup.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature. Mix well until well blended. Drop on ungreased cookie sheets by a teaspoon. Flatten with a fork, leaving indentations. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: crab or salmon souffle
directions: Dice 4 slices of bread and place in 9 x 13 greased dish. Spread the first 5 ingredients that have been mixed together over the diced bread. Remove crust from remaining bread and place bread over top of the mixture. Beat eggs and pour in milk. Pour over crab mixture and press down lightly with spoon. Refrigerate overnight. Bake 15 minutes at 325°. Remove from oven. Spoon soup over top and sprinkle with cheese and paprika on top. Bake for 1 hour more.

title: biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add other ingredients and knead a little.
Roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut as biscuits; brush both sides with butter.
Let rise 1 hour, then bake at 400°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and allow to chill overnight. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: brunch roll-ups
directions: Mix eggs, softened cream cheese, salt and pepper (a dash), crumbled cooked crispy bacon, ham, green onions, cheese and milk together well.
Cook until done but not dry (real moist).
I use microwave on Medium and stir in between time until done.
Do not overcook.
Fill each tortilla shell with egg mixture.
Serve warm with salsa and chips or jellies.
For decoration you can arrange roll-ups in a circle to make a wreath with salsa bowl or jelly bowl in the middle.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly, except bacon and tomato sauce.
Put into loaf pan, cover with bacon.
Pour the tomato sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together. Serve with fresh fruit. Double recipe for more dip.

title: nancy's dream cake
directions: Drain juice into measuring cup.
Mix cake mix according to package directions, except use pineapple juice for liquid and substitute milk for rest of water.
Add crushed pineapple and bake according to directions on box.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil. Heat in 350° oven for 10 or 15 minutes until softened.

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in casserole.
Mix together flour, sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour over oleo.
Add fruit.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jamaican bunn
directions: Mix sugar, butter (melted), beaten eggs, evaporated milk and browning until dissolved.
Add flour, baking powder, raisins, currants, minced meat, wine and Stout; mix well.
Add salt to taste.
Pour into greased baking loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain all fruit well and combine with coconut and nuts. Sprinkle dry pudding mix over fruit and fold in.
Add Cool Whip and fold again.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: If mushroom soup, add 1 cup mayonnaise.
Mix all together.

title: strawberry meringue bars
directions: Beat shortening, 1/3 cup sugar and 2 egg yolks.
Add sifted flour.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Spread mixture in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and spread evenly with 1 cup preserves.
Stiffly beat two egg whites then gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold in 1 cup nuts.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Soften the unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Combine the chocolate and water; stir over low heat until blended.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin until dissolved.
Beat 3 egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar until light.
Add chocolate mixture, dash of salt and the vanilla.
Cool.
Beat 3 egg whites.
Add 1/2 cup sugar. Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate curls.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise in half.
Slip out yolks.
Mash with fork.
Mix in seasonings, mustard, Miracle Whip and relish. Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it up lightly.

title: mater sandwich extrodinaire
directions: Take two pieces of fresh loaf bread.
Spread with regular mayonnaise liberally, but not excessive, on one side of each piece of bread.
Gather a fresh tomato from the garden in season, remove peel and radially slice, beginning from the bottom side, in slices approximately 3/8-inch thick.
Cover one piece of bread, mayonnaise side, with tomato slice or slices being careful to remove any hard spots that may exist in tomato.
Apply salt and pepper to tomato slices to suit individual taste.

title: shrimp over rice
directions: Mix together.
Heat until hot; serve over rice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Blend in the egg until fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture. Stir in vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Add pie filling, cinnamon and ginger, beating well. Cover and chill for 8 hours. Serve with gingersnaps, apples or pear slices.

title: oatmeal flapjacks
directions: Combine Campers Mix and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir until blended.
Pour batter onto hot, lightly greased griddle.

title: carol's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Press in pan (9-inch) and 1-inch up the sides.
Combine cottage cheese and Egg Beaters until smooth.
Combine with rest of ingredients with mixer.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until set. Cool in oven for 1 hour with door ajar.
Chill at least 2 hours. Garnish with lemon slices if desired.
Top with fruit.
One-half fat per serving; 145 calories.

title: cauliflower - pea salad
directions: Prepare bite-size pieces of cauliflower.
Add peas (cooked and cooled).
Add onion.

title: grandmother lovie byrd's caramel cake
directions: Bake in 3 large or 4 small layers. Spread with
Caramel Icing.

title: barbara's chili
directions: *To reduce fat, may substitute 1 pound turkey (ground).

title: chocolate cookie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease two round cake pans.
tags: Betty Crocker chocolate fudge cake mix

title: easy apple streudel
directions: Mix first three ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate until completely chilled or overnight.
Cut pastry in half and knead several times, then roll into oblong shape.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute garlic and onion until golden brown.
Add the beaten egg; stir, then add the cooked rice and put in the soy sauce and bacon.
Cook until it blends mixture together.

title: tempura
directions: Using cold water (about 40°) is a must.
This keeps the batter from becoming sticky. When you add the flour, whisk quickly just to mix it in evenly.
Sticky batter results in oily tempura.

title: "7 can soup"
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat.
Wonderful.
I put in a crock-pot and when ready to eat, it is ready.
Good with Mexican cornbread. So good - so easy!

title: tasty chicken
directions: Boil chicken
in
water for 12 minutes.
Add 1/2 spices and 1/2 sauce.	Cook 15 minutes; drain water.
Add more spices and sauce.
Cover
chicken.
Let
cool	for
15 minutes.
Cook chicken on grill about 10 minutes each side.
Add any barbecue sauce. Grill 10 more minutes.

title: calzones
directions: Cook meat and onion until brown; drain fat.
Remove from heat. Stir in the sauce, olives, basil and oregano.
Cut a thin slice from top of each roll.
Hollow out bottom of roll to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Sprinkle about 3 tablespoons cheese into each roll bottom.
Spoon meat mixture over each.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Replace roll tops.
Wrap individually in foil and refrigerate or freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Cook Rice-A-Roni mix as directed, adding onion and celery to mixture as cooking.
When done, mix broccoli, Rice-A-Roni, soup (undiluted) and cheese together. Sprinkle cornbread crumbs or Progresso bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bread crumbs are brown.

title: sausage and pepper italiano
directions: In covered skillet, over medium heat, cook sausage in 2 tablespoons water for 5 minutes, uncovered.
Cook until sausage is brown.
Add green peppers, onions and garlic to sausage.
Cook until peppers are tender-crisp.
Stir frequently.
Spoon off fat. Stir in soup, 1 cup of water and vinegar.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or longer.

title: fettucine
directions: Cook noodles for 12 to 14 minutes; drain and set aside.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet; add other ingredients.
Mix together until hot.
Pour over noodles; toss until the noodles are mixed well.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: minestrone
directions: Heat oil in large kettle.
Add next 4 ingredients until tender but not browned.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until macaroni is done.
When eating you can top your serving with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken dish and dressing
directions: Mix well. Put in buttered dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
