title: russian tea
directions: Boil water, sugar, cloves, and cinnamon for 15 minutes. Remove from heat, add tea, cover and let stand for 3 minutes. Strain.
Add strained lemon and orange juice, water, and sugar. Put back on heat and turn to medium heat.
Lower heat to where the tea stays warm but never boils.
Keep warm for 2 hours, and it doesn't ruin.

title: giant popovers
directions: About 1 hour 20 minutes before serving, start heating oven to 375°.
Butter 8 (6-ounce) custard cups.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk and melted butter. Beat until blended, then beat in flour and salt. Pour batter into custard cups to within 1/4-inch of top.

title: cracker candy
directions: Boil together sugar and milk 3 minutes only. Then pour over crumbled crackers, peanut butter, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients; pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Mix last 4 ingredients; spread over top of potatoes.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: oatmeal caramelita bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips and nuts.
Sprinkle over baked crust. Combine caramel ice cream topping with flour.
Mix well and pour over chips and nuts.
Press remaining crumbs on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Chill before cutting.

title: burrito pizza
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Stir in chili seasoning mix, stewed tomatoes and kidney beans. Cook 5 to 10 minutes. Arrange 8 burrito-size flour tortillas in a circle on a large pizza pan, overlapping edges. Spoon beef mixture onto tortillas. Top with 2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese and black olives. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken soup with vegetables and rice
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, add salad oil and cook carrots, celery and onions until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
With slotted spoon remove vegetables to a bowl.

In same Dutch oven heat chicken, parsley sprigs, bay leaf, chicken flavored bouillon, salt and six cups of water to boiling (high heat). Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for about 20 minutes or until juices run clear when chicken pieces are pierced with a knife. With slotted spoon remove chicken to another bowl and refrigerate until easy to handle, about 15 minutes.
Discard bones from chicken and cut into bite sized pieces.

While chicken is cooling, add vegetables and rice to broth in Dutch oven, over high heat bring to a boil and reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until rice and vegetables are tender.
Add chicken to Dutch oven and return to boiling.
Discard bay leaf and parsley sprigs.

title: apricot-nut loaf
directions: Place flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar in mixing bowl. Add eggs and oil; beat until smooth.
Add apricots and mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and stir in.
Prepare 2 (9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch) loaf pans by lightly greasing with oil and coating with flour. Divide batter evenly in the two pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Let cake cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on cake rack to cool.
Makes 2 loaves.
This cake may be baked in a 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Increase baking time to about 2 hours or until done.

title: kraut salad bavarian
directions: Combine ingredients in salad dish.
Chill and serve.

title: yeast corn bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water and stir to dissolve. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
This makes a stiff batter.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pan (foil pans).
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes.
May use for sandwich bread or toast and butter.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, cracker crumbs, onion, milk, egg, salt and ginger in a large bowl and mix well.
Shape into tablespoon size balls.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add mashed bananas.
Bake at 325° in 2 loaf pans 1 hour.

title: old fashioned fruit cake
directions: Dredge fruits and nuts with 1/2 cup flour.
Set aside.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Cream until fluffy.
Add Karo syrup to mixture and mix well.
Add 1 cup dry ingredients and beat well. Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add orange juice and mix well.
Add fruit mixture, folding in remaining dry ingredients. Bake in a tube pan greased and lined with brown paper bag.
Bake 4 to 5 hours at 250°.
Add a small pan of water in lower shelf of oven the last hour of baking.
May decorate cake with fruit and nuts before baking.

title: old fashioned hot salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.
Serve with warm tortilla chips.
Refrigerate unused portion.

title: potato bake
directions: Saute margarine, celery and onions.
Pare and boil potatoes in salted water.
When done, prepare for mashed potatoes.
Mix into potatoes the slightly beaten egg, the bread slices, onions and celery.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put in a greased baking dish.
Set oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour. Cover first half hour and uncover for remaining half hour.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: cherry pudding or cobbler
directions: In one bowl, place the first 4 ingredients and set aside.
In another bowl, mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour flour mixture into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spoon cherry mixture carefully over flour mixture (do not stir).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cherries go to the bottom and crust will be golden brown when done.
Never double this recipe.

title: rhubarb pie filling
directions: Beat egg, combine with dry ingredients stirring until smooth. Stir in rhubarb.
Place filling in bottom crust; cover with top and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with 2 cups of crushed cornflakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: coming-of-the-kings bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast from hot roll mix in 1/2 cup warm water (120° to 130°).
Stir in mix, eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla until mixed. Cover with towel; let rise in warm place away from draft until double, about 1 hour.
Stir in walnuts, raisins and 1/2 cup mixed candied fruit.
Turn dough onto well floured surface; knead until elastic and not sticky, about 5 minutes. Shape into 20-inch long roll; join ends to form a ring.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Cover with towel; let rise in warm place 30 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes (or until golden and sounds hollow when lightly tapped with fingers) at 375°.
Remove bread from cookie sheet to cool on rack.
When cool, in small bowl, combine 10x sugar and 1 tablespoon water.
Stir in remaining candied fruit. Use to glaze top of bread.

title: crab pate
directions: Heat soup in medium pan over low heat.
Remove from heat. Dissolve gelatin in cold water; let sit for 5 minutes.
Add soup and stir well.
Add the rest of ingredients and stir well.
Spoon into mold (4 cup) and chill until firm.
Garnish with parsley and serve with crackers.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Brown bacon and dice together with onion. Add ketchup and brown sugar. Pour over drained green beans. Bake 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered, then cover and bake 45 minutes more.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt; beat well.
Stir in semi-sweet morsels.
Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla to flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Fill cupcake pans 1/3 full of chocolate batter.
Top each with a heaping teaspoon of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and chopped nuts.

title: chunky cheese soup
directions: Wash potatoes and pat dry.
Prick each potato several times with a fork.
Arrange 3-inches apart on a layer of paper towels in microwave oven.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 8 to 10 minutes, turning and rearranging potatoes halfway through cooking time.
Let cool completely.
Peel potatoes and cut into chunks; set aside. Cook bacon in microwave dish for 5 to 7 minutes or until crisp. Drain bacon and crumble; set aside.
Combine beer, broth and Worcestershire sauce in 3-quart casserole.
Microwave at High for 3 to 4 minutes or until hot.
Combine half and half and cornstarch; stir well.
Add cornstarch mixture, cheese spread, milk and red pepper to beer mixture, stir well.
Cover and microwave at Medium-High for 4 minutes.
Serve in individual serving bowls using reserved crumbled bacon, shredded cheese and chives on top.
Yields 8 cups.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer except for chocolate chips. Fold chocolate chips in last with spoon.
Bake 1 hour or less at 325°.
Test with a straw to be sure it's done.
Let set in pan for a few minutes before turning out.

title: toast with creamed salmon
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Stir in flour until smooth; add onions. Gradually stir in milk. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Reduce heat; stir in salmon, salt and pepper. Let cook for 10 to 12 minutes, until thoroughly heated.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Mix all (do not drain cans) and let simmer for 1 hour or all day in a crock-pot on low heat setting.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Cream butter, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Spread on bottom and sides of 8-inch spring-form pan.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Saute beef in oil in a large pot until beef begins to brown. Add onions, carrots, celery and tomatoes and simmer for about 10 minutes. Drain and rinse beans and add to the pot.
Add beef stock, oregano, pepper, tabasco, spaghetti sauce and noodles. Simmer until celery and carrots are tender, about 45 minutes. Yields 3 quarts.

title: apple cake
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Pour in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy corn relish
directions: In a
saucepan,
blend starch and water.
Add the rest. Cook over medium heat.
Heat until thick and boiling.
Jar and seal. Let cook and check to be sure jars are good and sealed.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Clean and dry turkey inside and out.
Using a shaker, cover turkey inside and out with salt and pepper.
Heat enough oil to cover turkey to 325° to 350°.
Be careful to choose a pot big enough so that oil does not overflow.
Cooking outside is the only safe way to do this at home.
Put bird in pot slowly.
Fry about 4 minutes per pound, a little longer for bigger birds.
Test for doneness at thigh joint.

title: thai chicken with noodles(a la ralph and pam)
directions: Prepare chicken breasts.
Saute garlic, ginger and white part of scallions until tender.
Add chili; saute.
Add soy sauce, rice vinegar and sugar; continue to cook while stirring.
Add in reserved chicken broth and tahini; simmer.
Add diced chicken. Toss with boiled linguine or noodles.
Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed and chopped green scallions to garnish.
Place cucumber around edge of plate to present.

title: united states senate bean soup
directions: Mix beans, ham, onion and the rest of ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil; stir.
Lower heat and cover.
Boil gently for 45 minutes or until done.
Mash a few of the beans to thicken. Cook for 10 to 20 minutes more.
Freezes well.

title: tierney macaroni and cheese(diner style)
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan. Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly; add seasonings.
Cook until sauce is thickened.
Add 1 cup grated sharp Cheddar cheese and stir until melted.
Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain.
Add to cheese sauce and mix well.
Turn mixture into 8-inch square baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle top with the second cup of grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven (preheated to 375°) about 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and place under broiler until cheese is bubbly and lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oreo sundae
directions: Mix the cookies and butter together.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Press Oreo cookies in pan.
Slice ice cream in half and place over Oreo cookies.
Spread pecans over ice cream.

title: iced cucumber soup
directions: Cook potato in broth.
Saute cucumbers and onions until soft. Add potato and broth.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Put through blender.
Refrigerate.
Serves about 4 people.

title: spiced bananas
directions: Cut the bananas in long thick strips.
Sprinkle both sides of the slices with lemon juice.
Melt the margarine in a large nonstick skillet.
Stir in the cinnamon, honey and nutmeg.
Add banana slices.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes until golden brown.
Gently turn slices over and cook on all sides.
Serve warm.

title: cheese bread
directions: Beat cheese, sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle sesame seed over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Add sugar, salt and shortening to milk and scald over low heat until bubbles appear.
Add 3/4 cup water to milk mixture.
Mix yeast and lukewarm water to dissolve, add the two liquid mixtures together in a large bowl.
Add 2 cups flour and beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Remove from bowl, add remaining flour kneading until smooth and satiny (about 5 minutes).
Place in greased pan, cover, let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and divide into 2 loaves.
Place in well-greased loaf pans and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When bottom of pan is thumped, done bread will have a hollow sound.

title: spanish olive salad
directions: Rinse olives and slice in half.
Chop celery and add to olives.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Add onion and oil.

title: jake's snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill dough; shape into balls the size of walnuts and roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Press down gently and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and 1 cup mashed berries.
Boil and stir until thickened.
Add butter and lemon juice.
Line pie shell with the balance of uncooked berries. Pour sauce over berries.
Cool at room temperature.
Top with prepared topping.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a small bowl, mix the two cheeses with the oregano and set aside.
With a teaspoon, drop the cheese mixture evenly over the crust.
Scatter the broccoli, mushrooms, olive and tomatoes over the cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool five minutes before cutting.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tansy cakes
directions: Combine honey and butter.
Add eggs, then rest of ingredients. Beat until well blended.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle cookies with more tansy.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: veal chops with mushroom sauce
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Shake and coat each chop in flour mixture.
Heat oil in heavy skillet with garlic.
Add chops and brown on each side.
Drain off fat; mix mushroom soup with paprika, salt and marjoram and pour over chops. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, over low heat about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: Put steak into freezer for about 45 minutes. Cut steak into 1-inch strips.
Wash vegetables and break broccoli and cauliflower into flowerets.
Cut carrots, celery and onions on the diagonal. Slice mushrooms.
Stir-fry onion and celery together and remove from pan.
Stir-fry carrots, broccoli, cauliflower, snow peas, pepper and mushrooms separately and remove each from pan when finished.
Stir-fry steak, ginger and garlic until done.
Remove steak.
Mix together water, soy sauce, wine vinegar, bouillon cube, cornstarch and parsley together.
Add mixture to pan and cook until thick.
Add all vegetables and steak and heat through. Serve over cooked rice and top with chow mein noodles.
Other meats and vegetables may be substituted.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together in baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with topping.

title: fudge
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, butter, marshmallows, salt and milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it boils and is bubbly all over the top.
Boil and stir over medium heat 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate morsels until melted.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Cool.
Cut into about 30 pieces.

title: peppy tomato slush
directions: In a small pitcher, stir together tomato juice or vegetable juice, lime juice or lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish and hot pepper sauce.
Pour tomato mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and freeze for 1 to 2 hours or until slushy.
Spoon into glasses. If desired, garnish with celery sticks.
Makes 2 (8-ounce) servings.

title: glazed hot dogs
directions: Make sauce.
Pour over hot dog pieces.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with picks.

title: pecan brittle
directions: In heavy saucepan (I use a large iron skillet).
Mix sugar, water and syrup.
Cook, stirring, until sugar dissolves, using medium heat.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Stir in pecans and salt, stirring constantly.
Cook until hard crack stage.
Remove from heat and stir in oleo and baking soda.
This will bubble up quite a lot.
Pour out immediately on buttered cookie sheets.
Be careful, this is very hot.
If you wish thinner candy, stretch the candy as it cools.

title: italian chicken bake
directions: Rub the outside of chicken with salt and pepper.
Set aside. Stir the garlic powder into melted butter.
Set aside while preparing the bread crumbs.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, thyme and savory together until mixed.
Brush each piece of chicken in the seasonings.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican wedding rings
directions: Cream butter, salt and sugar.
Add other ingredients and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 20 minutes. They will not be brown.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
If preferred, when cooled, roll in powdered sugar again.

title: yummy nut fudge
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave at High (10) for 4 minutes Stir in peanuts.
Microwave at High (10) for 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Microwave at High (10) for 1 to 2 minutes more.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot. Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet or an unbuttered nonstick coated cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in an airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: pepperoni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Slice pepperoni in half.
Cube or shred cheese.
Chop tomatoes and olives.
Mix dressing mix, oil, vinegar, water and sugar well and pour over vegetables.
Chill for several hours before serving.
May be multiplied 2, 3 or 4 times.

title: soft play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan. Cook over low heat until mixture adheres into a ball (about 5 minutes).
Knead a little as dough cools.
Store in container to keep soft.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave oven with 2 tablespoons water. Thoroughly blend tofu in blender or a food processor. Add melted chocolate and vanilla to the tofu and blend for 2 minutes. Slice banana and layer with chocolate mixture in either pudding cups or graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. Garnish with remaining banana slices and almond slices if desired.

title: choco-mint freeze
directions: Toss together crumbs and butter.
Reserve 1/4 cup crumb mixture; press the rest into a 9 x 9
x 2-inch pan.
Spread with ice cream and freeze. Melt 1/2 cup butter and chocolate over low heat; gradually stir into egg yolks with the sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Beat chocolate mixture until smooth; fold in egg whites.
Spread chocolate mixture over ice cream; top with reserved crumb mixture. Freeze.
Makes 8 large servings.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly(makes 5 half pints)
directions: Grind jalapeno and bell peppers in food processor.
Combine ground peppers and their juices, vinegar and sugar in a 6-quart or larger pot; bring to a slow boil and boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in pectin.
Return to heat and bring to boil; boil rapidly for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and skim off foam. Quickly ladle into hot, sterilized jars leaving 1/8-inch headspace.
Seal.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crackers, cheese and onion and pour into greased casserole dish.
Pour tomatoes over cracker mixture. Dot with butter and bake for 30 minutes.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed.
Blend
together	soup and flour.
Add sour cream, carrot, onion, salt
and
pepper.
Stir in broccoli.	Turn into 2 quart
casserole.
Combine	stuffing mix and butter.
Sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until hot.	Serves 6.

title: smooth and creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in small bowl. Beat slowly with mixer at low speed until well blended, about 1 minute. Fold in whipped topping; spread on cake. (Store frosted cake in refrigerator.)

title: german's sweet chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool. Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy adding egg yolks one at a time.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk beating smooth after each addition. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured pans 3 (9-inch) layers.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, 1 (9 x 13-inch) layer 35 to 40 minutes and 10-inch tube 50 to 55 minutes.
Test (ovens differ). Frost with French Frosting.

title: squash patties
directions: Place squash and onion in colander.
Add salt.
Let drain until moisture is gone.
Combine drained squash, onion, cheese, flour, corn meal and pepper; mix well.
Stir in eggs.
Brush griddle with thin coating of oil and heat over medium flame. Using 1/3 cup mixture for each patty, fry until golden brown on both sides.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
In mixing bowl, combine blueberries, sugar, flour, lemon peel, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Pour filling into pastry-lined pie plate.
Drizzle with lemon juice and dot with butter.
Place top crust on filling; cut slits for escape of steam.
Seal and flute edges.
Sprinkle sugar on top of crust.
Bake at 400° for 35 or 40 minutes or until crust is done.

title: cheese crescents
directions: Stir sugar in warm milk and sprinkle yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes and stir gently.
Sift flour and salt in bowl.
Pour in yeast mixture now that a dough has formed.
Knead for 5 minutes and roll dough out in 4 or 5 inch rounds.

title: spinach quiche with rice crust
directions: Crust:
Mix the first 6 ingredients in a small bowl.
Spray a 9-inch quiche dish or pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Remove quiche dish from oven and reduce temperature of oven to 375°.

title: horseradish and beet sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill. Good with ham or hot dogs.

title: stir-fry rice
directions: Spray wok or large skillet with light vegetable oil cooking oil.
Saute onion over medium heat about 3 minutes.
Turn heat to high.
Add rice; toss constantly.
In a bowl, combine oil, sugar, soy sauce and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour oil mixture over rice.
Toss constantly until all is well mixed and no longer sticky.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise, vegetable soup mix, drained spinach and onion.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate until serving time.
If desired, serve in hollowed out loaf of pumpernickel or rye bread.
Serve with crackers or party pumpernickel or rye breads.
Makes about four cups dip.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly mix together brown sugar, salt, flour and spices. Add slightly beaten eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Stir in milk and water.
Pour in a 9-inch shell (unbaked).
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake for 20 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw & drain spinach. Mix ranch dip mix and sour cream; then add drained spinach. Refrigerate, serve cold.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Add the orange juice, ginger and nutmeg to the hot cooked and mashed sweet potatoes.
Beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form and fold them through the sweet potato mixture.
Spoon the potatoes into a nonstick dish and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add enough boiling water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve jello.
Stir in whole can of cranberry sauce and orange peel.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in oranges and pineapple.
Whip cream.
Fold it into fruit mixture. Pour into 6 cup mold.
Chill until set.

title: white roquefort dressing
directions: Add milk to mayo, then add remaining ingredients, slowing mixing at moderate speed.
This will thicken when refrigerated.

title: sour cream chicken and egg casserole
directions: Blend flour to a smooth paste with 1/2 cup of cold broth; stir into remaining hot broth and soup mix; cook and stir until thick. Blend in sour cream.
Pour over and alternate layers of chicken, eggs and mushrooms in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or heated and bubbly.

title: banana date bread
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Add sugar and nuts.
In separate bowl, mix remainder of ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stir until moistened.
Turn into greased 9 x 6-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375°
for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to cake rack to finish cooling.
Store overnight before slicing.

title: quick tater tot bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in greased 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with Tater Tots.
Combine soup with milk or water; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange date-nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat just to mix.
Add soda to flour and mix alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in grated orange rind.
Coat the dates and nuts with small amount of flour and add to mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in angel food cake pan.
Pour the following sauce over cake when it's done.
Let set until completely cool.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13 baker.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in a half strip of bacon.
Tear chipped beef in small pieces.
Spread in bottom of medium casserole dish.
Place chicken on beef, leaving a little space between chicken pieces.

title: glorified rice
directions: Make rice as directed on box using the pineapple juice and adding salt.
Let cool, then add crushed pineapple, marshmallows and cherries.
Whip cream with sugar or use whipped topping.
Fold into rice mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, vanilla, flour and salt.
Add nuts.
Chill for 1 hour.
Make balls out of dough and bake for 12 minutes at 350°. Cool, then cover with powdered sugar.

title: stuffed baked pork chops
directions: Combine bread crumbs, onion, butter, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cut pockets into pork chops.
Stuff pockets with bread crumb mixture.
Put chops in casserole dish.
Combine water and ketchup.
Stir well; pour over chops.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish crushed pineapple and apple pie filling.
Top with dry cake mix.
Place margarine pats over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and light brown on top, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
It's easy, it's quick and it's good!!!

title: spinach and garlic
directions: Wash spinach and pat dry.
Tear into pieces and remove thick stems.
Place in a large pan; sprinkle with salt, cover and cook a few minutes.
Remove spinach from pan and squeeze out liquid.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add the spinach, anchovies, garlic and pepper.
Stir to mix all ingredients.
Cook for 5 minutes over low heat.

title: best ever pet treats
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Make smaller droplets for cats.

title: pattie's fresh spinach salad "for 6"
directions: Wash spinach several times, changing water each time; drain well.
Refrigerate until needed (cover if keeping overnight). Slice carrots thinly lengthwise, then again lengthwise into "toothpick" size.
Slice onions very thinly; separate into rings. Slice olives thinly; mix with pimentos and set aside (refrigerate if keeping overnight).
Mix onions and carrots with dressing; cover and refrigerate.
Place spinach in serving bowl.
Top with all vegetables.
Add dressing.
Toss several times before serving.

title: rena's get well quick soup
directions: Add all ingredients in large dutch oven, saving rice until last.
Cook until leeks are clear and carrots are almost done (about 20 minutes on low).
Add rice and cook until done.
Season to taste.
Serves a bunch.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed ingredients, then add milk, vanilla and water.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. This has a delicious homemade taste!

title: broccoli casserole deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Blend sour cream and soup carefully with broccoli, carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix stuffing and margarine.
Spread over broccoli and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken crescent supper
directions: Cook chicken; debone and tear in small pieces.
Combine chicken and 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Separate rolls to 8 triangles.
Place 2 tablespoons of chicken on wide end of rolls. Roll up, beginning at narrow end.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery.
Drain off grease; add soup and catsup.
Let simmer 1/2 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer half of the potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat with rest of potatoes and onion.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over potato mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: divinity (never fail) candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, vanilla and water until forms a ball with dropped in water. Beat egg whites until stiff. Beat while you pour syrup over egg whites in thin stream. Beat until holds a peak. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper to cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain and mash the squash.
Dice the onion.
Melt margarine; pour over crumbs.
Cover bottom of dish with 1/2 the bread crumbs. Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over crumbs.
Pour balance of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tea punch
directions: Mix well and chill.
Makes a pitcher full.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, egg yolks and 1/2 of the milk to form a paste.
Add the remainder of milk, flour and vanilla; cook in microwave for six or seven minutes.
Stir after the first 3 minutes.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture with wafers ending up on top. Beat egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla to make meringue.
Spread on top of wafers and brown in oven. Serve hot or cold.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, Wesson oil and eggs. Beat good.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in greased and floured pan.
Frost with vanilla icing.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, chocolate, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust lined pan.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Cook together flour and milk, stirring constantly, until thick like custard.
Refrigerate until very cold.
Then cream together Crisco, oleo and sugar until no longer grainy.
Then add flour mixture and vanilla and continue beating until very smooth and creamy.

title: super-duper chocolate cookies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate; add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add with nuts; mix well. Chill dough for several hours.
Form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: west virginia salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl the first 6 ingredients.
Add sugar. Top with the mayonnaise, grated cheese and crumbled bacon. Before serving, mix all together.
This can be made the night before and you can add the vegetables you like.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese and cracker crumbs; mix well. Alternate layers of eggplant mixture, cheese and cracker crumbs in casserole.
Butter last layer of cracker crumbs; sprinkle on top. Bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Serves 12.

title: easy and delicious coconut cake
directions: Prepare as directed on box. Bake in 3 cake pans. Adjust cooking time to approximately 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: apricot kugel
directions: While noodles are boiling, melt margarine in oblong pan in 350° oven; blend (in blender) sugar, apricots and eggs.
Drain noodles and pour into pan; mix in apricot mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top; bake 45 minutes.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: In a casserole pan add uncooked ground meat, crumbled up, then spread can of cream of celery soup over the ground meat.
Then put the Tater Tots on top.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: In a heatproof 9 x 9-inch dish, layer the ingredients.
Spread the cream cheese first, then the chili (skim off fat) and finally the cheese.
To spice it up, add the hot peppers.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn and cherry tomato salad
directions: Combine yogurt, ketchup and mustard in a large bowl.
Stir in green onions and dill.
Set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add broccoli and cook until tender. Add mushroom soup, mushrooms, and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 300° until bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, garlic and green pepper.
Drain well.
Place in large pot.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Cook over low heat to simmer flavors 1 to 2 hours. (You may need to add some water if sauce becomes too thick.) Serve over your favorite cooked pasta.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Heat at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in a small greased casserole. Serve warm with crackers.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Combine all other ingredients in a pot.
Cook slow until marshmallows are melted.
Pour on cool cake.
Spread ready made frosting on top of coconut mixture.

title: banana split cake
directions: Leave out 1 1/2 sticks margarine and 2 eggs at room temperature.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine and pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat balance of margarine, 2 eggs and powdered sugar for 15 minutes (no less).
Spread over crumbs, then spread drained pineapple.
Slice bananas lengthwise on top of pineapple.
Spread on Cool Whip. Sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.
Chill at least 5 hours.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Cut slaw mixture.
Sprinkle
1	cup sugar over it.
Let stand while you
bring
to
a
boil the oil, vinegar, salt and spices. Pour over
slaw
while
hot
and let stand overnight. Will keep in refrigerator for several days. I only put 1/2 cup sugar.
This is good
without
sitting overnight.
I also add some carrots.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add onion and cook over medium heat until onion is tender; drain. Stir in seasoning, tomatoes, soup, rice and olives. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with cheese.
Bake to melt cheese. Garnish with additional sliced olives.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Mix the next 4 ingredients. Pour over salad; mix lightly, but well.
Chill thoroughly.

title: pasta with salmon and asparagus
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Stir-fry salmon and minced asparagus in the 1/4 cup butter.
Add parsley and cream.
Simmer over low heat 5 minutes, whisking in flour.
Add white pepper to taste. Place pasta on 4 serving plates; top with sauce and sprinkle with cheese.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tan.
Add flour to skillet, then process in food processor.
Add chicken broth and pumpkin; puree. Add seasonings.
Heat to boil.
Stir; will stick.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes.
If too thick add milk while simmering, or add at the end of simmer time.
Remove from burner.
Add sour cream. Serves 4.

title: cheesy rice
directions: Heat rice, water and salt to a boil, stirring once or twice. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 14 minutes without lifting lid to stir.
Remove from heat; fluff rice lightly with fork.
Cover and let steam 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese and margarine.

title: dick's favorite apple pie
directions: Pare and quarter apples; then half each quarter crosswise to make chunks (should be about 7 cups).
Place in a large bowl. Combine flour, sugar and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over apples, toss to coat well.
Spoon into pie shell and drizzle with lemon juice. Sprinkle with topping to cover apples.
Slice into a heavy brown paper bag large enough to cover pie loosely.
Fold open end and fasten with large paper clips.
Place on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mideastern rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until translucent.
Add rice; saute for 3 minutes.
Add bouillon, cooked diced ham or chicken, cooked corn or peas and raisins.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in toasted almonds and serve.

title: flaschenkas
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and flour.
Chill.
Roll out thin like pie crust. Cut with 2-inch round cutter.
Spread 1/2 with ham and fold over like Parker House rolls.
Freeze if you choose or bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Watch close!
Makes approximately 75.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Melt the oleo.
Add garlic; saute until tender.
Bring to boil.
Add clams and whipping cream.
Bring to boil, then simmer 10 minutes, stirring.
It will cool and thicken in refrigerator, then warm up.

title: healthy alternatives spinach omelets(serves 4)
directions: Spray large skillet with olive oil Pam.
Cook on moderately hot stove.
Saute onion, mushrooms, red bell pepper, etc.
Lastly add chopped spinach (thawed or fresh washed).
Season to your liking. Add 2 containers egg substitute or you can split vegies and do 2 separate panfuls.
Sprinkle to your liking with Healthy Choice cheese, Weight Watchers Parmesan and any herbs or seasonings.
Cook over moderately low heat for several moments.
Then flip and continue cooking.
Top with sour cream and picante.
Enjoy!

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, cinnamon, sugar and soda.
Stir well and add beaten eggs and oil, stirring only until moistened.
Stir in berries and nuts.
Spoon in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour or appropriate time for size of pan.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Add soda to buttermilk and let set 20 minutes.
Coat sides of heavy sauce pan with butter.
Add sugar and buttermilk/soda mix and cook to firm ball stage.
Beat while cooling.
when mix begins to thicken add nuts and vanilla.
Pour on buttered plate or pan and cut into squares to serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: You will need a 9 x 13 glass rectangular pan.
Mix 1 cup boiling water with lemon Jell-O and let set. Then mix 1 cup sugar with cream cheese and set aside.
Then whip Carnation milk and vanilla.
Add all remaining ingredients together and set aside while you prepare your pan.
Mix 1 stick butter with cup of graham cracker crumbs.
Line your pan and pour your mixture into. Sprinkle with small amount of graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate until set, then cut and enjoy.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a 9 inch x 13 inch greased casserole dish. Melt margarine and pour over the top of potatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread over top of potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients together working dough well.
Add enough flour to make the consistency of biscuit dough.
Roll out and cut putting on a hot pan.
Bake until lightly brown in a 350° oven.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours. Serve with bread, crackers or vegetables.

title: slow cooker chili
directions: Place all ingredients in cooker at medium setting for 8 plus hours.

title: cheese roll
directions: Let Velveeta cheese stand at room temperature until soft. Blend well with cream cheese.
Add nuts and stir in.
Form into small balls, then roll balls into rolls.
Roll in chili powder. Store in refrigerator.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Cut shortening in.
Put milk in all at once and stir until dough forms a ball.
Fill centers with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter and wrap.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fruited cherry salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine the cherries, pineapple (with juices), sugar, flour and food coloring.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from stove; add the gelatin.
Cool until slightly thickened, then stir in the bananas and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crab dip
directions: On a plate or dish spread box of cream cheese.
Then spread cocktail sauce.
Chop crab meat into small pieces, and spread over top.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: In Dutch oven fry bacon, brown bacon and add ground beef. When beef is cooked, drain off grease.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for an hour or continue to simmer on stove until flavors blend.

title: collard greens and ham hocks
directions: Put ham hocks, onion, garlic and hot sauce in an 8-quart pot with enough water to cover ham hocks.
Cover and cook over medium heat until water comes to a boil.
After it begins to boil, remove the lid and let boil for 5 more minutes.
Stir in the salt (wine) and greens, then add the soy sauce and stir again; cover, then turn heat to low and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
If necessary, add more water so that greens don't stick.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash shrimp with cream cheese and onion.
Put out on a plate and pour cocktail sauce on.
Spread. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold. Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna and rice dinner
directions: Melt oleo in skillet on medium heat.
Add onion, cook and stir until tender, but not browned.
Stir in peas, milk, soup, and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Stir in tuna, minute rice and parsley. Cover, remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels with butter in double boiler.
Pour chopped pecans into caramel.
Dip onto greased cookie sheet.
When completely cool, dip into melted chocolate.
Place on waxed paper and let cool.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Put in pan chicken broth, onions (diced small), celery (diced) and oleo.
Cook until celery is tender.
Break up bread in large bowl, then add step 1 to the bread.
Add 2 eggs and mix well.
Add sage (sprinkles) until you can smell the sage lightly.
Add a dash of pepper.
Stuff in your turkey.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix seasoning packet from stuffing mix with melted butter or margarine.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine packet of bread crumbs from stuffing mix with corn, milk and egg.
Stir in seasoning and butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: no-bake chocolate mint cheesecake
directions: In small microwave-proof bowl, melt chocolate chips on High (full power) 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred; set aside to cool.
In large mixer bowl beat cream cheese, sugar and butter until smooth.
On low speed blend in melted chocolate.
Fold in whipped topping until blended.
Spoon into crust.
Cover, chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries and pineapple into a 13x9x2-inch pan, mix well. Spread dry cake mix evenly over mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and completely cover with very thinly sliced butter.
(To slice butter more easily, place in freezer a few minutes befire using.)
Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: easy turkey pot pie
directions: Mix together turkey pieces, soup, mixed vegetables and stock. Set aside.
Coat a 13 x 9-inch casserole with melted butter.
Pour out excess butter and reserve for later use.
Next, pour turkey veggie mixture into the buttered casserole dish.
Blend together the biscuit baking mix, milk and excess butter.
Blend until almost smooth.
Pour topping over vegetable and turkey mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Best when eaten first night.

title: fruit pizza
directions: For crust, combine the shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs and beat well.
Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix all together and chill dough for one hour.

title: broccoli and cheese kids will eat!
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain any excess liquid.
Put back in pan.
Shred Cheddar
cheese,
sprinkle on top of broccoli.
Let melt in oven or
microwave
for
about 5 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Layer ingredients in a greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Pour milk over mixture.
Top with crushed crackers or cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bettye's cabbage casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Chop cabbage; steam until tender and season with bacon drippings.
Drain cabbage.
In large casserole, layer cabbage, chopped bell pepper, sliced onion and then repeat layers.
Add chopped bacon and cover with mushroom soup.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: one-skillet sausage supper
directions: Place all the ingredients in a skillet in the order listed. Cook, covered, over medium-high heat for 30 to 35 minutes or until starts to brown.
Skillet will be really full at the beginning but will cook down.
Serves 4.

title: kris kringle krunch(holiday favorite)
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler or microwave at 50% power. Stir until melted.
Combine other ingredients in a large bowl. Pour melted white chocolate over all.
Mix.
Spread on waxed paper.
Let set.
Break into small chunks.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Serves many.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
Add 2 cups chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste.
Add chopped egg.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until the skins pop.
Cool.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together the graham crackers, sugar and oleo; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: southern fried okra
directions: If okra pods are large, you
may have to boil slightly to tenderize.
Cut off top and stem ends.
Slice pods into 1/4-inch slices.
Mix salt and pepper.
Roll in cornmeal.
Saute in hot drippings until tender and brown.

title: mexican rice
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add rice and onion and brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bring to boil.
Cover and put on low heat, stirring occasionally until liquid is absorbed.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown ground beef in frypan; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce; remove from heat.
Combine cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, green onions and green pepper.
Spread half of the noodles in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with the cheese mixture and remaining noodles. Pour melted margarine over the noodles.
Cover with meat mixture. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix the ketchup, water, onions, salt, vinegar, brown sugar, green pepper and dry mustard.
Pour over cut up cooked roast. Simmer the mixture with the spice bag for at least 1/2 hour.

title: coke cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Heat margarine, cocoa and cola until mixture boils.
Pour over flour and sugar; mix.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.

title: sand dabbs
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla. Roll by teaspoonful into small roll or fingers.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with ice pick.
Bring 1/2 to 3/4 cup apricot nectar and 1/2 to 3/4 cup powdered sugar to boil and pour over cake.

title: easy corn casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Heat margarine in 1 1/2-quart pan. Pour other ingredients over margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: turkey-spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on box.
Drain and rinse.
Combine spaghetti and remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased shallow 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place a layer of sliced sweet potatoes in a 2-quart greased baking dish.
Add a layer of the orange or apple slices.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and top with small pieces of margarine if desired.
Repeat until all ingredients are used. Pour orange juice (or apple juice) over the top and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars, then add eggs.
To this mixture add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, allspice, cloves and salt.
Then stir in fruit cocktail (after juice is drained off) and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Melt caramels with water and margarine over low heat.
Stir frequently until sauce is smooth.
Combine sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Gradually add caramel sauce and mix well.
Stir in nuts and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Pie filling will appear to be very soft, but will become firm as it cools.

title: even better chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and brown sugar.
Add milk, vanilla and egg. Sift flour, salt and baking soda together; add to creamed mixture. Stir in milk chocolate chips, mini M&M's and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: virginia hot dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans and butter.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Saute pecans in butter and place on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: dublin coddle(irish)
directions: In saucepan combine broth, sausage, bacon and 1 cup water. Bring to boiling and boil 5 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove sausage and bacon.
Reserve broth.

title: summer squash
directions: Boil 2 pounds sliced summer squash and chopped onion for 10 to 15 minutes and drain.
Mix cream of chicken soup with sour cream. Add drained squash.
Mix stuffing with 1/2 cup margarine.
Put part of stuffing on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer squash mixture over that and sprinkle with grated carrot.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown hamburger in microwave for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Shred cabbage.
Cook in microwave covered for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook in microwave covered for 10 to 15 minutes covered.
Pour into crock-pot and cook 4 to 5 hours on high or 8 to 9 hours on low.

title: cook-up rice
directions: Boil black-eyed peas until tender.
Fry up chicken, onions, garlic, thyme and scallions until chicken is cooked.

title: one layer choc-choc cake
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over very low heat. Stir constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour. Blend in yolks, one at a time. Beat egg whites until foamy throughout.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Continue beating until soft peaks will form.
Gently fold chocolate mixture into egg whites. Blend thoroughly.
Pour in greased and floured 8-inch layer pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes (cake will continue to cool upside on rack).
Spread top and sides with Chocolate Glaze. Garnish with chopped pistachios.

title: butter crunch crust
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients
with hands.
Spread in oblong pan (13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch).
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir with spoon.
Save 3/4 cup for topping.
Press rest of mixture against bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Cool. Pour in lemon chiffon or a creamy pie filling.
Sprinkle the rest of the mixture over top.
Chill one hour before serving.

title: karo coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add syrup, sugar, flour, salt, milk and coconut.
Mix
well.
Pour
into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for about 50 or 60 minutes, until a knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: geneva's crunchy egg salad
directions: Combine eggs, peas, onions and water chestnuts with mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or more.
Just before serving, lightly toss in noodles. Reserve a few to sprinkle on top.

title: chicken pasta casserole
directions: In skillet over medium heat put 1 tablespoon oil in.
Add chicken pieces and brown.
Add soup, water and vegetables with pasta.
Heat to a boil, cover and cook over low heat about 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix well and add nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 1 hour and 30 to 45 minutes at 330°.
Use a toothpick to test center.
This is a very moist bread.

title: joey's seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Layer next 3 ingredients over crust.
Pour milk on top. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 12 bars.

title: fresh or frozen corn
directions: Use a glass bowl and add fresh or frozen corn.
Add enough water to cover corn.
Mix 1/2 cup of flour with water (hot works best); stir until dissolved and no lumps.
Mix with corn and add butter, salt and pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Take out and stir down very well.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Remove plastic wrap carefully to avoid burns.
This can be doubled for larger quantities.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups whipped topping and blend thoroughly.
Spread over crust; chill.
Combine pudding mixes and milk.
Beat 2 minutes with rotary mixer at medium speed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer.
Garnish with pecans and/or chocolate.
Yields approximately 15 servings.

title: maple syrup sauce
directions: Cream butter in bowl until softened and smooth.
Gradually add and beat in the sugar; beat until blended.
Add egg yolk and beat well.
Mix in the maple syrup and vanilla and beat until creamy. Whip egg white until it forms stiff peaks; whip the cream until stiff.
Fold beaten egg white and whipped cream into butter mixture. Good over squares of warm uniced cake.

title: corn bread surprise
directions: Make each corn bread mix according to directions on box.
Pour half of bread mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Arrange American cheese slices over top of corn bread mixture, enough to cover.
Sprinkle green chilies over cheese.
Pour rest of corn bread mixture on top of chilies and cheese.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: chicken alberghetti
directions: Dip chicken breasts in egg-milk mixture, then in mixture of bread crumbs, Parmesan, salt and pepper.
Saute quickly in olive or vegetable oil until golden.
Pour half of marinara sauce in baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts.
Cover with cheese slices and other half of marinara sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly throughout. (325° if using a glass dish).

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Measure ingredients into containers.
Seal and shake. Refrigerate several hours.
Shake before serving.
Makes 1 cup.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix night before and refrigerate.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350°
oven.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix well. Form a ball and roll in chopped pecans. Chill overnight.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts.	Salt and pepper them.
Mix cranberry sauce, salad dressing and dry soup mix.
Pour over chicken,
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes. Sauce will thicken.
Good served over rice.
Serves 6.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese; add rest of the ingredients.
Put in pot to keep warm.

title: orange pineapple cheese salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice with sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Stir until it boils.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add water and chill until mixture thickens enough to keep the cheese and nuts from going to the bottom.
Fold in cheese, nuts and whipped topping.
Refrigerate in tight container.
This makes a large salad.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Combine and cook until thick all but sweet potatoes.
Put sweet potatoes in casserole.
Add sweet potatoes.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Saute green pepper, celery and onion in oleo in a large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.

title: aunt ruby's ruby red tea
directions: Place tea bags in boiling water.
Remove from heat and allow to steep for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar; stir. In a 2-quart pitcher, combine tea, juice, lemonade and water.
Mix well.
Chill and serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon.
Serves 5.

title: orange frost
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Cool 10 minutes. Add oranges, marshmallows and sherbet. Chill to consistency of egg whites. Add cream cheese by small bits. Fold in Dream Whip (prepared). Pour into mold or large pan. Chill until firm.

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Stir together egg, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add pecans and raisins.
Bake in an 8 or 9-inch square pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cookies are soft when taken from oven. Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all
together.
Add, all at once, into a casserole. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Saute chicken in margarine seasoned with lemon pepper.
Take out chicken and mix 1/2 cup of rice and onion in margarine.
Mix one cup of rice and chicken stock together.
Mix with the rice, onion and margarine mixture.
Add chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay carrots on top.
Cover and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued chicken pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place pizza crust on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread crust with barbecue sauce, then top with chicken, cheese, olives and bell pepper.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until pizza is crisp and cheese is melted.
Remove from oven.
Makes 8 slices.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour batter into hot pan and cook in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except blueberries.
Blend until smooth (mixture will be very thick).
Gently fold in blueberries.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan or on cake rack for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until smooth.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well. Mix with sauce and italian seasoning.
(Just sprinkle until you think it's enough.) Heat thoroughly, Mix 1 egg with cottage cheese and parsley flakes. Spoon enough sauce on the bottom of large baking

dish to cover it. Be sure the dish is not too large to go into the microwave. Layer noodles, cheese slices, and cottage cheese mixture (be sure the last layer of noodles are ample covered with cheese and cottage cheese; even a bit of ground beef if there is enough to go around. Cover with Saran Wrap and microwave on high for 9 minutes then on power level 7 (simmer) for 35 minutes.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in a greased casserole (9 x 13-inch) dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then dump in all others.
Mix well, then dump into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar before baking.

title: eggplant italian
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Saute onion and garlic.
Remove from heat.
Add cottage and Mozzarella cheeses, bread crumbs, herbs, salt and pepper.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, arrange half the eggplant. Spread with cheese mixture, then add another layer of eggplant.
Layer top with sliced tomatoes. Cover with 2 cups marinara sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Cover and bake for 25 minutes. Uncover and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and Crisco.
Add the crushed vanilla wafers.
Make into small balls after adding the sugar and orange juice.
Roll in coconut or pecans.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: shamrock pie
directions: Melt the chocolate over hot water; spread evenly on a sheet of waxed paper.
Let cool until firm.
Press lightly oiled shamrock-shaped cookie cutter sharply into chocolate, or cut around a shamrock pattern.
Leave shamrocks on the waxed paper and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: peggy's "little devils"
directions: Remove yolks, blend with salt, vinegar and Miracle Whip.
Fill egg cases.
May top with bacon bits.
The vinegar gives these eggs a different taste than most deviled eggs.
I'm always asked what I do different, and it's the vinegar!

title: taco filling
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add sauce and spices and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk, vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix vegetables and milk mixture into drained macaroni. Refrigerate until served.
Serves a lot of people.

title: kahlua candied yams
directions: Cut yams in serving sized pieces.
In heavy skillet, melt butter with sugar.
Add Kahlua; cook 1 minute.
Add yams.
Turn until brown on all sides.
Cover, reduce heat and cook about 15 minutes.
Turn yams once more before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, vanilla and sweetened condensed milk in bowl.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Mix in the other ingredients well.
Bake on one crust.
This makes 2 pies.

title: parmesan tomato bake
directions: Combine tomatoes and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat until clear and thickened.
Stir in onions.
Pour vegetables into 1 quart casserole dish.
Combine cheese, egg and salt; mix well. Spoon rounded ??? of cheese mixture around edge of the casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: moravian rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except noodles and nuts.
Put into baking dish and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with noodles and nuts and bake 10 minutes longer.
Water may be added during baking if it gets too dry.

title: dessert cheese ball
directions: Mix pudding powder and softened cream cheese.
Add drained fruit.
Shape into ball and chill.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: maco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 475°. Spread cream cheese evenly in an ungreased 10-inch casserole dish; set aside. In saucepan over low heat, mix beans, garlic, onion and salt. When mixture is hot, add 1/2 cup cheese and mix until melted. Spread mixture over cream cheese; top with remainder of shredded cheese. Bake first 10 to 15 minutes uncovered. Then cover with tinfoil and bake another 10 to 15 minutes or until sides have bubbled a few minutes. Remove from oven; remove foil. Let cool 2 to 3 minutes. Serve hot with chips.

title: "lazy day" chicken and dressing
directions: Mix celery soup, chicken soup and milk together.
Melt chicken stock and oleo.
Layer chicken and pour soup mixture over.
Top with stuffing.
Pour oleo-stock mixture over stuffing, moistening all the stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes in a large casserole dish.

title: peanut blossom cookies(delicious cookies to add to your christmas tray)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the chocolate kisses.
Mix on low speed until dough forms.
Shape into small balls (using teaspoon for each).
Roll balls in sugar.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Add broccoli, chicken and most of the cheese (save some to lightly cover top). Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly.

title: fudge squares brownies
directions: Mix and bake for 30 minutes in a moderate oven at 350°.
When cool, they can be iced.

title: moonwalk cake dessert
directions: Boil water and butter.
Take off burner.
Add flour.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Spread onto cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely for 1/2 to 1 hour. Mix pudding, milk and softened cream cheese.
Spread over crust and let set 1 hour in refrigerator.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top.
Return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli and rice according to package directions. Drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients; stir lightly, but thoroughly, and pour into a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Heat thoroughly in oven or microwave.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: my dad's barbecue sauce
directions: Chop celery, onions and garlic in food processor until very fine.
Saute in butter until tender.
Add lemon juice and vinegar and mix well.
Add ketchup, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Add sugar.
Bring to boil and continue to cook on low for a few minutes.
Add water to thin if you like.

title: miniature beef wellington
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
When hot, add mushrooms; cook until tender. Add wine.
Cook just until liquid is evaporated.
Stir in green onion, thyme, salt and pepper.
Remove from skillet and cool thoroughly. Heat same skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Place steaks in skillet; cook three minutes, turning once. (Steaks will be partially cooked.
Do not overcook.) Season with salt and pepper. On flat surface, layer phyllo dough, spraying each sheet with cooking spray.
Cut stacked sheets lengthwise in half.
Stack halves together, then cut in half crosswise to make two equal stacks.
Place two tablespoons mushroom mixture in center of each portion.
Place steaks on mushroom mixture.
Bring together all four corners of phyllo dough; twist tightly to close. Lightly spray each with cooking spray.
Place on greased baking sheet. Immediately bake at 425° for 9 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: pecan candy
directions: Pour evaporated milk into a pot.
Add butter or margarine and sugar.
Bring to a boil, then add vanilla extract.
Cook at a low heat
for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring constantly.
As candy begins to harden, gradually pour in pecans. (Candy may be tested by dropping drops of the mixture into a cup of tap water, if candy hardens, it is cooled.)
Pour candy on a greased cookie sheet.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together margarine, cream cheese and flour.
Form into even balls.
Shape mixture in muffin tins.
Add fillings.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a skillet or wok at medium-high heat 2 minutes.
Add eggs; cook 1 minute on each side.
Remove from skillet; chip and set aside.
Heat remaining 3 tablespoons oil in skillet or wok; add ham or pork and stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until golden.
Add bell peppers and onions; stir-fry 5 minutes. Add peas and next 3 ingredients; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Stir in reserved egg and sprinkle with green onions.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the meat and onion. Add water with both mixes and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in rest of the ingredients and simmer 15 more minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over both sides; pound into steak.
Cut into serving pieces.
Melt shortening in pan over medium heat.
Brown meat well on both sides.
Combine vegetables and spread over meat.
Cover; reduce heat to low and simmer until meat is very tender, approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Remove meat and thicken remaining sauce.
Pour over steak.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix thoroughly oil and cocoa; blend in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla; add sugar.
Mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix cocoa mixture and flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoons into confectioners sugar and roll into balls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ham hocks and turnip greens
directions: Thoroughly wash the greens, breaking off the tough stems. Place them in a pot with ham hocks and red pepper pods.
Cover with boiling water and boil gently for 3 hours.
When done, season to taste with salt and pepper.
Drain, reserving the cooking liquid.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in cake mix and flour.
Let rise until double in size; punch down.
Roll in rectangle; spread with brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Roll jelly roll fashion, slice and place on buttered cookie sheet.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jello punch
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Pour over Jell-O.
Mix in flavoring and juice.
Measure the mixture and add 1 1/2 times as much water. Freeze.
Thaw before serving, 4 to 5 hours.

title: butter toffee
directions: Combine sugar, salt, water and butter.
Cook to light crack stage (285°).
Add 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Pour into well-greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Spread 1/2 of chocolate on top with 1/2 cup walnuts. Cool.
Turn over.
Spread with remaining chocolate.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup nuts.
Break into pieces.
Makes 2 dozen pieces.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in 1/3-inch slices.
Cook in boiling salt water until tender; drain.
In saucepan, cook shredded carrots and chopped onions in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups herbed stuffing, chicken soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt the remaining butter.
Add 1 cup stuffing and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: yummy slaw
directions: Mix slaw mix, onions, and almonds.
Break noodles into small pieces and sprinkle on top. Mix last 6 ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Toss vegetable noodle mixture with dressing just before serving.

title: louisiana pralines
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium heat until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Beat well and add pecans.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Combine ingredients together; bring to a boil, stirring. Cool.
Pour into freezer trays or popsicle containers.
Freeze.

title: homemade pepperoni
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except beef. Add beef mixture, then divide into thirds.
Put on the shiny side of foil, then roll into cylinders about 10-inches long and the thickness of your thumb and forefinger together.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Take out and poke holes into foil.
Put on broiler pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine and mix well first 4 ingredients; add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.

title: red velvet cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth. Roll into 1-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Use bottom of a glass to flatten slightly. Bake at 375° until the top crackles (8 to 10 minutes). Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown ground turkey with onion and pepper.
Add seasoning. Put in large pan with remaining ingredients.
Cook to boil, then simmer for 30 to 60 minutes.
Add more seasonings, if necessary.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Bake in shallow dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain grease.
Pour tomato sauce across top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and lay in a jelly roll pan.
Bake as directed.
Cool 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise together.
Spread over baked dough.
Sprinkle with finely chopped mixed vegetables.
Top with the Cheddar cheese and press down. Chill and cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.

title: steak 'n vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a large skillet and brown steaks.
Remove steaks from skillet and add onions to drippings.
Saute until tender.
Reduce heat.
Stir in mushrooms, soup, buttermilk and seasonings.
In a 3-quart casserole, place a layer of half the potatoes, half the carrots, 3 steaks and half the soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake covered for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Remove cover and continue to bake another 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: pink salad
directions: Prepare jello as directions on package.
Refrigerate until it begins to set.
Add Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator until completely set.

title: oatmeal sandwich cookies
directions: Add soda water last.
Mix ingredients in order given.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat in mixer for 20 minutes 2 sticks margarine, confectioners sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with the crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan (bottom).
Spread filling on crumb mixture.
Spread pineapple over.
Slice the bananas on top. Spread Cool Whip over all.
Decorate with walnuts and cherries. Refrigerate overnight or 4 hours before serving.

title: golumbki
directions: Try to buy cabbage with large fluffy leaves.
Cracked leaves can be used to line baking pan.

title: pumpkin pecan muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Stir in dressing.
Add pumpkin and pecans; mix well.
Mix flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir flour mixture into pumpkin mixture.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer on medium speed.

title: jamie's blueberry cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and granulated sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Combine the flour, salt and baking powder and add alternately with the milk to the creamed mixture.
Stir in the blueberries and pour the batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Mix together the brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter and sprinkle over the batter.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breasts florentine
directions: Cook spinach pouch according to directions.
Pound chicken lightly to make cutlets 1/4-inch thick.

title: homemade bread
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt in processor with steel blade already in processor.
Make one turn of processor to mix.
Add butter; turn on and off.
Add yeast and water; turn on and off. Add 1/3 cup cold water; quickly blend.
Let dough rest.
Butter bowl and pan; clean up mess.
With machine running, add more water slowly until ball forms.
Let ball rotate about 1 minute, then place dough in greased bowl.
Turn and cover; let rise until double.
Knead until elastic.
Place in pan; let rise again. Preheat oven to 400°.
Put bread in; reduce heat to 325°.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: dr. erikson's glogg
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil, then boil slowly for 30 minutes.
Strain and reserve liquid.
Add sugar, wine and vodka or brandy.
Heat and serve with blanched almonds and raisins.

title: sour cream noodle delight
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown meat; add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Simmer
for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients, except the noodles and cheese, and mix.

title: energy bars
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In medium mixing bowl, beat butter until fluffy.
Beat in honey, egg, vanilla and orange rind.
Beat in the dry ingredients alternately with the orange juice.
Stir in coconut and carrots.
Pour into a greased or parchment-lined 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Trim brisket.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice onion on top. Sprinkle celery salt on top of brisket.
Pour small amount of Worcestershire sauce on top, then pour liquid smoke on top.
Cover with foil.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, drain liquid.
Place in 250° oven for 5 hours.
Last hour, pour bottle of barbecue sauce over brisket and cook.
Melts in your mouth.

title: beet pickles
directions: Put cooked beets in mixture and boil.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: butterscotch icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Then take soda and flour and mix well together.
Mix together with sugar mixture.
Form into 3 or 4 narrow loaves.
Put in a cold place overnight.
Then cut slices and place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Place everything except sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Stir in sugar, cover and simmer 30 minutes until tender.
Serves 6.

title: no-fat - no-cholesterol cheesecake
