directions: Combine cream cheese, Marshmallow Fluff (whole jar), eggs and flour beat them until creamy.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown on edges.

title: pumpkin pie dessert squares
directions: Crust:
Mix cake mix (reserve 1 cup), 1/2 cup butter (melted) and 1 egg.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; grease bottom only.

title: microwaved creamy mashed potatoes
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish combine water, 3/4 cup milk, margarine and salt.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 5 to 7 minutes or until heated through.
Stir to dehydrate potatoes.
Stir in cream cheese.
Add milk if necessary until of desired consistency.
Cook, covered, on High about 1 minute or until heated through.
If desired, top with margarine and chives.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini carrot bread
directions: Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, beat eggs and oil; stir in brown sugar, zucchini, carrots and vanilla.
Sift in flour, etc.
Add bran and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: big c bread
directions: Combine beaten eggs, oil and milk.
In a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add egg mixture; mix just until thoroughly combined.
Stir in carrots, coconut, cherries, raisins and pecans.
Turn into 4 well-greased and floured 16 ounce fruit cans.

title: butter-rich cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flavoring.
Blend in flour and salt. Shape dough into roll about 2 inches in diameter.
Roll in pecans. Wrap; chill for about 4 hours.
Cut roll into 1/8-inch slices; bake at 400° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Reserve juice from blueberries and pineapple.
Use the juice for 1/3 cup of the liquid.
Add drained berries and pineapple to jello.
Chill until firm.
Spread with topping.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add onion soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and cream of chicken soup.
Butter casserole, sprinkle layer of crumbs on bottom of casserole.
Add squash mixture and generous dots of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy mock enchilada casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in casserole.
Finish with cheese on top. Simmer in oven until hot and cheese is a little brownish on top.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine in skillet.
Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix gently.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey dijon pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta, cauliflower, broccoli and celery for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Add remaining ingredients and combine thoroughly but gently.
Chill.

title: southwest cornbread dressing
directions: Cook hen and keep broth.
After hen cools, cut into small pieces.
Place these pieces on bottom of well-buttered 9 x 12-inch Pyrex.

title: minnie's sweet pickle sticks
directions: Mix spices, vinegar and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Wash cukes and cut into sticks.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 4 to 5 hours.
Drain and pack cukes solidly in pint jars.
Pour hot liquid over cukes.
Leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal jars and then process for 5 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Place chocolate and butter in a double-boiler and melt. Meanwhile, beat eggs until frothy and light, about 3 minutes.
Add confectioners sugar to egg mixture and beat well.
Combine chocolate mixture to egg mixture and walnuts.
Mix well.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Chill 1/2 hour and cut into small squares.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Beat eggs, salt, oil and milk.
Blend in flour until smooth. Take stock from beef roast to cover bottom of pan; have it boiling.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with gravy.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Beat eggs; mix in milk, then add butter, salt, cheese and bread crumbs.
Pour into a pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Flavor can be varied with different types of cheeses and the addition of herbs.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat eggs, mix other ingredients together, pour in casserole dish.

title: sand tart cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar together; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, salt, soda and flour.
Chill dough.
Roll out very thin. Cut with cookie cutters.
Brush top with milk.
Sprinkle with colored sugar or cinnamon sugar or sprinkles.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable fettuccine
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add next 7 ingredients.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add cream and bell pepper; bring to boil.

title: confetti spaghetti
directions: Fry the pepperoni in large skillet until edges curl.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Toss together cooked spaghetti, cheeses, tomato and oregano.
Add pepperoni, onions and pepper strips.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and whipped topping.
Add chicken, celery, grapes, almond and olives.
Toss mixture well.
Serve salad on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: indian lentils and spinach
directions: Heat butter in large saucepan.
Cook sweet pepper, onion, garlic and curry powder in hot butter for 1 minute.
Stir in lentils, broth, water and black pepper.
Simmer, covered, about 30 minutes or until lentils are tender and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Transfer to large serving bowl; add spinach and toss mixture until spinach is wilted.
If desired serve with mint and yogurt.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter. Sift dry ingredients, stir into creamed mixture.
Shape 1 teaspoon of dough into a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press dough with floured fork to make a crisscross.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: jogging juice
directions: Mix juices and vinegar together.
Drink 2 ounces before breakfast.
Good for what ails you.

title: corny corn bake
directions: Stick of butter must be soft so you can melt it.
Beat eggs slightly.
Salt and pepper.
Combine all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes up to 1 hour.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Remove skin, if desired.
Garlic salt and paprika your chicken on both sides.
Place chicken in baking pan.
In bowl, combine soup and cream; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with parsley and almonds. Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cake flour crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Set aside.
Cream butter, vanilla and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in the eggs and milk; beat well.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan and lightly press crust on the bottom.
Set aside until ready to fill.

title: bread roll
directions: Let bread rise.
Roll both loaves into a rectangle about 1/2-inch thick.
Brown ground meat, sausage and onions.
Drain. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spread meat evenly on the dough.
Roll dough starting on long side, like a jelly roll.
Put roll on cookie sheet.
Curve dough into a horseshoe shape.
Brush with cooking oil.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Remove foil at the end of cooking time so it will brown.

title: arizona skillet dinner
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion, green pepper and spices. Saute 4 minutes. Stir in tomatoes.
Add beans and corn. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Add macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream eggs, butter, vanilla, bananas and pecans.
Mix all together well.
Pour in well-greased tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and bake in a pie shell for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; mix with spaghetti sauce, cottage cheese and water.
In a large greased casserole, alternate noodles, meat sauce and grated cheese (end with cheese on top). Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes; cut and serve.

title: golden cheese spoon bread
directions: Heat milk in a saucepan until hot, not boiling.
Gradually add cornmeal.
Stir constantly.
Stir in salt and 2 tablespoons butter.
When butter is melted, remove from heat and stir in green pepper, corn and cheese.
Gradually stir hot mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold in.
Turn into a buttered baking dish (about 1 1/2 quarts). Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Pass warm melted butter to pour over each serving.

title: paczki
directions: Scald milk and allow to cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle in yeast. Cream butter and sugar mixed with mace or nutmeg until fluffy. Add egg yolks and whole egg, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and milk, gradually beating until well blended.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down. Knead, adding more flour, if too soft to handle.
Cover.
Let rise again until double.

title: baked sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put on 12 to 14 sandwich buns. Wrap each in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until hot and cheese melts.
May be frozen and baked at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: danish pastry
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients lightly to make pastry, spread on ungreased cookie sheet in 2 pieces 3 x 12-inch.
Bring to boil 1/2 cup butter, 1 cup water and almond flavoring; remove from stove. Add flour and eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Spread on pastry; bake 1 hour at 350°.
When cool, top with frosting, maraschino cherries and slivered almonds.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in salted water until tender.
Cut bread slices into small pieces.
Drain squash.
Add butter and egg; mix well. Add bread crumbs or pieces; mix well.
Fold cheese into mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spread cracker crumbs on top of squash and bake for 5 or 10 more minutes.

title: crab english muffin snack
directions: Mix cheese spread, mayonnaise, butter, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Fold crab meat in by hand.
Spread mixture on English muffin halves.
Bake in oven at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes. Remove and cut into 8 equal pieces while still hot.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl except for tortillas and cheese. Dip tortilla pieces into mixture and layer in oil-sprayed baking dish. Add layer of sauce on top of tortillas, then layer with cheese. Repeat process ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces if it is a whole chicken. Wash and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper.
In a skillet heat butter, garlic and 2/3 of olive oil.
Brown chicken on both sides (about 10 minutes).
Lower the heat add the herbs and continue cooking on low for about 20 minutes.
In a seperate skillet heat 2 Tbsp. oil and saute onion until clear and add mushrooms and 2 Tbsp. water.
Simmer 8-10 minutes and add to chicken.
Cover and simmer chicken for about 15 minutes.
Pour in sherry and turn up heat, boil for 1 minute.
Serve hot.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and marshmallow until smooth. Fold in yogurt; chill.
Good with cantaloupe, bananas, strawberries, apples and grapes.

title: mexican cornbreadmidland, texas
directions: Saute onion and chili in oil and add to dry ingredients.
Mix in egg and honey.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: vanilla orange popsicles
directions: In a large mixer bowl or blender, beat together the ice cream, orange juice and egg. Gradually beat in milk.
Pour in Tupperware popsicle molds or small waxed paper cups.
Insert sticks into paper cup molds when partially frozen.
To serve, peel off paper cup.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Cook meat.
Saute mushrooms, onion, garlic and peppers. Slightly beat eggs.
Mix together in greased baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: krusciki (angel wings)
directions: Beat egg yolks, sour cream, vanilla, whiskey and salt. Then add enough flour to make a dough that holds together. Knead until smooth and dough doesn't stick to hands. Roll out very thin. Cut into strips about 1 1/2 x 4-inches. Make a slit in the center of each strip and turn inside out. Fry in deep hot grease; dough will bubble a little. After dough rises to the top, turn over and fry about 1 minute. These are very fragile, so handle gently. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Cut up apples, oranges and bananas.
Mix all fruits with enough salad dressing to moisten or use the dressing as a topping on the salad when served.
Makes 6 servings, about 2/3 cup each.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 3 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Sprinkle cake with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and loosen cake with knife.
Flip over onto a powdered sugar towel.
Roll up towel in jelly roll fashion and cool for 45 minutes.
Mix filling ingredients together.
After cake has cooled, unroll and spread cake with filling and reroll. Refrigerate until served.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Add gelatin, softened cream cheese, pimientos, celery and nuts.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: green salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add dressing as salad is being served.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef and pork together.
Mix in beefy mushroom mix. Form into loaf.
Pour gravy over loaf in a large baking dish. Arrange mushrooms in gravy.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together in 2 1/2-quart casserole: chicken and onion.
Blend soup and broth and add to chicken and onion.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°.

title: corn custard
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: liza's special blueberry pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry 4-inches larger than the pie pan.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour over this crust.
Mix berries with remaining ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Trim edge of crust, leaving 1/2-inch overhang.
Moisten edge of crust with water.
Roll remaining pastry into circle 2-inches larger in diameter than pan, making a few slits.
Place over berries and fold under crust over top crust.
Press edges to pan with floured fork.
Brush top with milk or cream.
Bake in hot oven 50 to 60 minutes.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate.
Fold into cream cheese mixture with pecans.
Spread into a greased 8-inch baking dish.
Chill until ready to serve.
Cut into squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw frozen potatoes.
Mix with other ingredients except margarine and corn flakes.
Place in large casserole dish, cover with crushed corn flakes, drizzle melted margarine over the top. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Then uncover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: walnut jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cool water and cool until begins to thicken.
Mix diced apples with sugar and lemon juice. Add celery, pickle and chopped nuts.
Fold into jello mixture and chill until firm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and bell pepper in a skillet until brown. Mix cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and Velveeta cheese in a pan until cheese is melted. Combine the meat mixture and the cheese mixture. Pour over tortilla chips in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer chips, then mixture, topping off with chips. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Boil water; add jello.
Whisk Miracle Whip into the jello. Add applesauce and cranberry sauce mixture.
Spray 5-cup jello mold.
Pour mixture into mold slowly and allow to thicken.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken; bone and cut up.
Soak bread in broth, 2 1/2 cups.
Saute celery and onions in oleo.
Combine all.
Bake like dressing at 350°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Use 1 bowl microwave method to prepare instant potatoes while browning hamburger.
In glass mixing bowl or casserole, layer hamburger, green beans, tomato soup, potatoes and cheese.
Microwave until cheese is melted and beans are hot.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Beat yolks with sugar.
Add water and flavorings.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Beat well 5 minutes.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Mix 3 tablespoons butter with 1 cup brown sugar and add pineapple.
Put pineapple mixture in the bottom of the pan.
Put batter in an 8-inch square pan.
Bake 40 minutes in a moderate oven.
The cake alone (without pineapple mixture) can be used for shortcake.
Very good.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Serve with Fritos, tostadas, etc.

title: vegetable lasagne(low-fat)
directions: Saute onion in water with chicken bouillon cube.
Add carrots and spinach.
Cook until tender.
Add mushrooms and jar of spaghetti sauce.
Season with some brown sugar to taste.
Cook lasagne noodles, then take a casserole dish.
Spread sauce to cover bottom.
Layer noodles.
Top with sauce.
Continue to layer, topping each layer with some of the 3 cheeses.
Last layer should be sauce.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted well.

title: chocolate nut crunch
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and nuts.
Spread 1/2 the mixture in a shallow pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add chocolate and flavoring.
Beat egg yolks and add.
Stiffly beat egg whites and fold in.
Spread over crumb mixture; put other half of crumbs on top and chill overnight.
Serves 12.

title: crock-pot barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Add soup mix and barbecue sauce. Cook on low setting for 8 1/2 or 9 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: *Egg substitute may be used in place of the whole egg.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Add to a lightly greased casserole dish chopped broccoli. Saute celery and onion in butter.

Mix cream of chicken soup with sauteed onion and celery in separate bowl, then add rice. Stir well and spread over broccoli. Spread cream of mushroom soup over rice mixture. Cook at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Sprinkle grated cheese. Put back in oven until cheese melts good.
Serve.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in 4-cup glass measure.
Cook 2 minutes on High.
Stir.
Cook 6 more minutes on High.
Will be light golden.
Add the vanilla and butter and cook 1 1/2 minutes longer.
Add baking soda.
Stir in and pour onto a buttered cookie sheet that's a little warm.
Cool and break.

title: old fashion vinegar roll
directions: Combine vinegar, 1 cup of the sugar and 2 teaspoons of the cinnamon.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook over medium heat 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Put in shortening; stir in milk with fork until a soft dough forms.
Roll out into rectangle.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Roll up, starting at longer side.
Cut crosswise into slices about 1 1/4-inch thick.
Place out side up close together in deep baking dish.
Dot with remaining butter and sprinkle over remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over all.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot with heavy sour cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet until meat crumbles. Drain well.
Stir in corn, beans, tomatoes and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Pour into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Mix cornbread according to package directions and pour over mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make meatballs and fry them in shortening; cook halfway and simmer in sauce for 40 to 45 minutes, until ready to serve.

title: belgian waffles
directions: If possible, use a Belgian waffle maker.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt
the
oleo
and
cheese
in microwave or in top of double boiler.
Sift sugar and cocoa together, then add butter and cheese.
Mix together thoroughly.
Pour in large ungreased pan. Slice and serve.
Yields 6 pounds of fudge.

title: tessie coppley's open-face apple pie
directions: Put apples in unbaked 9-inch deep pie crust.
Combine sugar, flour and salt; stir in cream.
Pour mixture over apples; sprinkle with apple pie mix or cinnamon.
Cover pie loosely with aluminum foil and bake in 375° oven for one hour.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer or until apples are tender.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add lemon rind and walnuts.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and while still warm, spread with a mixture of the juice of one lemon, mixed with about 4 tablespoons sugar.
When the loaf cools, this forms a sugary crust on top.

title: faye craig's chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Spread chicken in baking dish.
Mix together cream of celery soup and cream of chicken soup.
Pour the soup mixture over the chicken.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook in a double boiler:
sugar, flour, salt, egg and milk until thickened.
Then add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Melt butter, add celery and onion, saute for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour, add stock and milk.
Cook until soup has thickened. Stir in celery leaves, salt and pepper.
Garnish with pimento.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix frozen lemonade and Eagle Brand condensed milk together. Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well, then pour into pie crust. Chill for about 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Whip cream until it stands in stiff peaks and fold into mixture.
Pour into crusts.
Allow to chill in refrigerator 4 hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peach crisp
directions: Put in microwave dish.
Put in peaches, then mix and add remaining ingredients. Cook about 10 to 12 minutes on full power, uncovered, turning dish halfway through cooking time.
Makes 6 servings. Contains 285 calories per serving.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Mix beans and seasoning mix.
Beat together cream cheese, sour cream and taco sauce.
Layer in order in dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with taco and nacho chips.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a deep casserole, layer beans, cheese and onion rings. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil and simmer, uncovered, 2 hours.
Freeze in separate containers according to your family size.
When thawed, heat thoroughly and serve with grilled cheese sandwiches.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil; add vanilla.
Add zucchini.
Sift and add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add chopped walnuts.
Bake in 2 well-greased loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: no salt seasoning
directions: Make applesauce as usual.
Measure.
For each 2 cups of applesauce, add 1 cup sugar.
Mix in enough cinnamon to taste.
A sprinkle of cloves may be added.
Put in large pan (I use dishpan). Cook in 350° oven for 3 hours.
Take out and stir every 30 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Melt the first 2 ingredients together. Take off heat and add green food coloring and vanilla. Stir in cornflakes (I use Frosted Flakes, stronger) until coated good with marshmallow mixture. Pour into greased jelly ring.
Press lightly to form wreath effect.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes, then unmold into 9-inch pie taker.
Let cool and set before cutting.
For decoration, use cinnamon candy to make holly berries. Can keep up to 8 weeks in Tupperware pie taker.

title: hungarian nut roll
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in milk. Add all other ingredients, small amounts at a time and mix well. Refrigerate at least 10 hours.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from top of peppers, remove seeds and wash. Brown ground beef and onion until done; drain.
Stir rice, garlic salt, and one can of tomato sauce.
Stuff peppers with mixture and stand upright in a baking dish.
Pour other can of tomato sauce over peppers and cover dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 more minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese on top.

title: dressed-up black-eyed peas
directions: Mix ingredients and cook for 25 minutes.

title: mom's au gratin potatoes and ham
directions: Boil potatoes in water for 30 minutes.
This can be done ahead. (Or microwave 5 to 7 minutes and refrigerate.)
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: marsha's healthy pumpkin pie(sugar free, low cholesterol, low sodium)
directions: Heat oven to 375.
In a bowl mix dry ingredients.
Stir together enough to mix all dry ingredients into pumpkin.
Add milk and beat until smooth.
Spray two 8-inch pie pans with non stick Canola spray and pour mixture into pans.
Bake just until knife comes out clean when tested in center of pie.

title: prime roast
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add bread and saute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased, crumbed bread loaf pan or in greased muffin tins.
Serve with gravy or cranberries. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and set aside.
Melt margarine in saucepan; blend in flour and add remaining ingredients except beans.
Cook until well blended and thickened.
Mix gently with drained beans.
Pour in casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan, stir together flour, sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Mix milk, oil and vanilla into flour mixture.
Stir with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts, then spread in pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cocoa and brown sugar over batter.
Pour the hot tap water over batter. Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon in dishes, top with ice cream and spoon sauce over each serving or serve alone.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla and carrots.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: herbed oven "fried" chicken
directions: In small bowl combine crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken strips in water, then crumb mixture.
Press crumbs to thoroughly coat.
Spray baking sheet with Pam.
Arrange chicken on sheet and sprinkle evenly with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° until tender, about 20 minutes.

title: deer soup
directions: Cook approximately 1 pound deer meat in slow pot overnight. (Meat will fall apart.)
In a large stew pot, boil chopped potatoes, onion and noodles until tender.
Add deer meat to soup and simmer.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine corn meal, salt, sugar, oil, water and half the milk in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Add eggs and the remaining milk.
Pour into a hot greased baking dish, 1 1/2-quart size.
Serve hot.

title: swedish pecans
directions: Toast pecans on cookie sheet at 325° until lightly brown. Fold sugar into egg whites and beat again to stiff peaks.
Fold toasted pecans into egg whites.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread nut mixture in pan and bake 30 minutes.
Turn mixture with spatula every 10 minutes.
Let cool a bit, then break apart.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Cook until soft state, stirring constantly.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, beat until holds shape.
Add nuts, if desired, pour into buttered pan.

title: hamburger-rice casserole(2 quarts)
directions: Brown meat in frying pan.
Add onion and cook until golden. Add pepper, salt, green pepper, rice and tomatoes.
Stir together well. Pour into greased 2-quart dish.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes at 400°.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.
Stir occasionally while baking and if necessary add tomato juice.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Make dough out of first 4 ingredients.
Turn into a 2-quart greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour water over chips.
Let stand until melted.
Pour over dough.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes to cool slightly.
During baking, pudding goes to bottom.
Dip sauce over cake in bowl. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet with a little margarine, salt, pepper and sugar.
Drain.
Mix ground
beef with green peppers, tomatoes, tomato sauce and water in a large stockpot or dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until green pepper is soft.
Add rice and simmer until rice is cooked.
You can also add 2 to 3 cloves of chopped garlic with the onion and beef if desired.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water just until frothy.
Add pecans and mix until all nuts are coated.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle over nuts, stirring nuts frequently, until nuts seem to be coated thoroughly.
Place on a buttered jelly roll pan (10 x 15 inches).
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: german coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour dressing over all. Let stand at least 4 hours.
Will keep in glass jars in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: carrot bars
directions: Combine butter and sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir into creamed mixture. Fold carrots and raisins into batter.
Spoon batter into a greased 13 1/2 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan or Pyrex dish, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.
Spread cake with a thin layer of lemon frosting.
Cut into 1 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch bars after frosting has set.
Yields 42 bars.

title: hot rye pizza squares
directions: Brown meats together and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except bread.
Mix and heat until cheese is melted.
Spread on rye slices and freeze on cookie sheets.
When frozen store in plastic bags.
To serve broil until bubbly.

title: white chocolate cream cheese fudge
directions: Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well, add vanilla and nuts, mixing until well blended.
Quickly beat in melted chips.
Put in a pan sprayed with vegetable spray.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: melt 'n moments
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat.
Beat in flour and cornstarch.
If dough is too sticky, add a few drops of milk. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until very light golden brown.
When cookies cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
One recipe makes 45 cookies.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole; top with buttered corn flake crumbs.
Bake in 300° oven for about an hour.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies. Pour into Cool Whip and ice cream. Mix well. Freeze in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheese faces
directions: First we get a spoon.
Then we get a bowl.
Then we put the salad in the bowl.
Then we put in the popcorn.
Then we put in water and sugar and then smash it with a smasher.
Then we put in butter.
Then we put it in the oven.
And then scoop it up and eat it.
We will also have grapes with popcorn and popcorn juice with it.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon, onions and egg.
Combine flour, baking powder and 2 tablespoons reserved liquid.
Mix into salmon mixture.
Spoon into deep fat and brown quickly.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 12 to 15 croquettes.

title: interstate 45-minute cream cheese cake
directions: Combine melted butter or margarine, egg and cake mix; spread mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine softened cream cheese, eggs, brown sugar, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt; beat until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cake mixture. Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes or until cake is brown.
Cut into small squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 48 (1-inch) squares.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Saute mushroom caps in butter until just soft.
Drain on paper towels until cool.
Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Mix sausage and cream cheese together and put into mushroom caps.
Place in a baking dish and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: In a large bowl, mix the cranberries, sugar and marshmallows. Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add shortening.
Put egg and vinegar in a 1 cup measuring cup; fill to 3/4 cup measure with water.
Mix with fork and press in pie pan.

title: cherry cheese charmer
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Drain cherries, measuring syrup; add water to make 3/4 cup as necessary. Add syrup and lemon juice to Jell-O.
Gradually blend Jell-O into softened cream cheese. Chill until very thick.
Then whip until fluffy.
Fold in drained cherries.

title: beaver's tail (biberschwanz)
directions: Skin, wash, clean and dry the tail.
Cook in half water and vinegar until it is tender.
Remove it from the pan.
Cut into suitable pieces.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in breadcrumbs.
Fry in hot butter or other fat until a golden brown.

title: almond cookies
directions: Combine sugar, flour and almonds. Add egg white, butter and vanilla, stirring well. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto parchment paper-lined baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden. Cool on baking sheets before removing. Store in airtight container.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Cook pasta according to package instructions.
Brown ground beef until well done.
Add envelope of French's seasonings.
Mix well.
Add both jars of Ragu sauce.
Slowly mix in tomato sauce and sugar.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer sauce, noodles and cheese in order, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° until middle begins to bubble, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: suffolk pumpkin
directions: Open pumpkin top (as in carving a jack-o-lantern) and scrape insides, disposing of all seeds and strings.
Mix all ingredients and spoon into pumpkin.
Replace top and spray outside thoroughly with Pam.
Bake in a shallow dish in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Spoon warm fruit into bowls and top with whipped cream or serve as a side dish with turkey or chicken.

title: judy turner's brownies
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, one at a time, mixing each ingredient well as you add it.
Pour in greased and floured Pyrex.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: souper corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Stir all ingredients together and cook in an 8-inch pan.

title: cold weather soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.

title: turkey parmesan(293 calories)
directions: Dip turkey cutlet into beaten egg.
Coat with mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Arrange on greased baking pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven for 5 minutes to heat sauce and melt cheese.

title: egg casserole
directions: Put eggs, milk, onion
and
green
pepper into blender. Cover and process at "chop"
until
onion and green pepper are finely chopped.
Pour into
large	skillet and cook over medium-high heat, stirring
constantly	to
scramble
eggs.
Spoon cooked eggs into a greased
2 quart casserole.	Pour soup over eggs and top with cheese slices.
Cover with lid and refrigerate for at least 8 hours or overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh strawberry ice milk
directions: Place strawberries in container of an electric blender or food processor; process just until chopped.
Sprinkle strawberries with 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Combine remaining 1 cup sugar and skim milk in a saucepan; sprinkle gelatin over mixture.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cook mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar and gelatin dissolve.
Gradually stir in egg substitute; cook mixture 1 minute.
Remove from heat; chill.
Stir in strawberries, evaporated skimmed milk, vanilla and food coloring. Pour into container of a 1-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Pack ice milk with additional ice and rock salt; let stand 1 hour before serving (ice milk will be soft).
Garnish, if desired.
Yields 16 servings (148 calories per 1-cup serving).

title: *exquisite pie
directions: Mix together well the butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and vinegar.
Then add raisins, coconut and pecans.
Put into 2 unbaked 8-inch pie shells and bake at 325° for an hour.

title: marinated vidalia onions
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper. Add onions and carrots. Toss well and cover. Refrigerate 24 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: cherry delight
directions: Grease 8 x 9-inch cake pan (glass works best).
Spread cherries on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of cherries.
Cut margarine into pats.
Evenly distribute pats on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Great with vanilla ice cream.

title: art's stroganoff
directions: About one hour before beginning to cook, marinate fresh beef (or chevon) in the wine.
I often cut up the meat directly after butchering (or buying) and freeze the amount I'm going to need for each stroganoff meal.
I then put the frozen meat directly into the wine and let it sit for two hours, rather than thaw the meat out and then marinate it.

title: laban
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
When milk rises to top of pan, remove from heat and allow to cool.
In a large Pyrex bowl, mix starter until smooth.
As soon as milk has cooled, when you can hold finger in milk and count to 10, pour milk into bowl, stirring very well.
Cover tightly with lid and heavy bath towel.
Keep in warm place for at least 7 hours or overnight until thickened (do not disturb).
Remove excess water by placing terry cloth over Laban. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water until dissolved.
Add pineapple and strawberries.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into dish and chill.
When set, pour sour cream over this, then add remainder of mixture on top of sour cream and chill until top layer is set.

title: darlene's italian soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat.
Stir in spices from Hamburger Helper mix.
Add corn, tomatoes and juice and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Heat to a boil.
Then reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in noodles and simmer for 10 minutes longer.
Serve; sprinkle with more cheese.
Makes 10 cups.

title: breakfast of champions
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Fry sausage and drain.
Put on top of bread.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups of grated cheese on top of sausage. Beat eggs and milk together. Pour over top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: best broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to boil; add rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Saute onion and celery until tender.
In mixing bowl, combine rice, celery and onion with remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Yields 6 servings.
Yummy.

title: pork with sauerkraut for sunday dinner
directions: Combine sauerkraut, cabbage and water in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Make a well in the center and place pork in. Simmer with the lid on, stirring occasionally, approximately 3 hours. Add knockwurst about 1/2 hour before finished.
Pork is done when cooked through and breaks apart with fork. Add brown sugar if sauerkraut tastes too sour. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: carotene rich minestrone soup(heart healthy)
directions: In soup pot, melt butter with oil.
Add onion and leek and cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and 2 cups water.
Stir in carrots, potatoes, bay leaf, thyme, oregano, sage, salt and pepper.
Heat to a boil; reduce heat to medium and simmer for 35 minutes.
Add beans, 1 can water, chili mac noodles, escarole, broccoli, parsley and basil.
Cook an additional 20 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, sugar and eggs with sour cream.
Pour half of the mixture into greased baking pan.
Make filling by mixing brown sugar and cinnamon.
Spread half of the filling over batter. Pour in remaining batter and then spread with remaining filling mixture. Swirl with knife blade. Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla and milk for glaze.
Pour over warm cake.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice cut carrots, cook until tender and drain.
Cut peppers in thin strips.
Combine soup, sugar and dill; bring to boil. Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Cool, then add all ingredients. Chill overnight.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Combine dry milk, flour and seasonings in a 3-quart heavy pot. Stir in water and condensed chicken broth until smooth.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Briefly saute onion in margarine.
Stir onion mixture and broccoli into thickened mixture.
Continue to stir until broccoli is heated.
Pour into soup serving bowl.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Add parsley as garnish.
Serve immediately.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Add 1 teaspoon soda to 1 cup sour milk (cream).
If doesn't fizz, add a few drops of vinegar.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Combine powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs, nuts and oleo. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and lemon juice and pour over the crust.
Bake 20 minutes in 325° oven. Cool and spread blueberry pie filling over top.
Spread Cool Whip on and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: meatless stuffed zucchini
directions: Clean zucchini; peel lightly and cut off stems.
Cut in 3-inch lengths.
Run apple corer through center of the zucchini lengthwise and pull out the center.
Chop the centers very fine and add bread crumbs, then cheese, egg, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pack in hollow zucchini.
Roll any remaining stuffing into small balls.
Place balls and zucchini in baking dish and pour spaghetti sauce over all; cover.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: fresh tomato casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 each tomatoes, onion, cracker crumbs, sugar and salt in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish (casserole).
Repeat with remaining half.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, then spread sour cream on top.
Sprinkle croutons over sour cream and pour melted butter over that.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: swedish cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Chill 30 minutes.
Combine walnuts with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll dough in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: "chuckwagon butter thin" pancakes
directions: Mix cream and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix all together, then add 1/2 pound hot butter.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth; follow your rice directions for cooking time.
When rice has been cooked, then season with seasoning mix and pepper.
Add sprouts, mushrooms, onions and soy sauce.
Add 1/2 cup oil and simmer about 5 minutes on low heat. Bake sesame seeds in a shallow pan and place under broiler until popping and add to rice.
Add your cooked chicken that is cubed to rice mixture.

title: tart lemon squares
directions: Combine 1 c. flour and 1/3 c. powdered sugar in a bowl; cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press mixture firmly and evenly into the bottom of an 11 x 7 baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Cut 4 tomatoes into 6 sections almost to stem end.
Using a sharp knife, peel back the skin of each section to form petals.
Fill each tomato with egg salad; top with a scoop of Miracle Whip.

title: bananas foster
directions: Over medium/high heat with saucepan, add brown sugar, butter and heavy cream.
Mix to liquify.
Add banana liquor and dark Myers rum and mix.
Add bananas.
Turn once.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add cinnamon.
Remove from heat.
Serve over ice cream.
Cooking time should take no longer than 3 or 4 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Set aside. Combine cereal and milk. Let stand for 2 minutes. Add egg and oil. Mix well. Add dry ingredients, stirring until mixed well. Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Cook sugar, pecans, milk and butter to hard ball stage. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, beating until creamy. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.
Serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients in a dish in same order given.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix together pulp and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add soda to buttermilk; stir until foaming stops and add to mixture and stir.
Sift flour; add salt and baking powder.
Sift into persimmon and buttermilk mixture and beat well.
Add cream.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into batter, leaving enough to grease pan well.
Beat mixture well.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Mix well.
You may have to add more flour in order to have dough stiff enough to roll into layers.
Bake at 375° in iron skillets.
Put cooked dried apples between and over layers while still slightly warm.
Season apples with spices and sugar to taste.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Mix
together.	Put
in
refrigerator for 25 to 30 minutes, then roll out and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: garlic beans
directions: Soak overnight; drain and serve.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and po`ur into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry blender relish
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water, in saucepan for five minutes. Warm over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Place cranberries, orange, apples, sugar and gelatin mixture into blender.
Cover and blend until orange peel is finely chopped.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled. Garnish with halved orange slices.
Makes 4 cups.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt cheese and 1/2 stick margarine in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Stir in Veg-All.
In another container, mix 1/2 stick margarine and 1 stack crushed Ritz crackers.
Add crumbs on top of Veg-All mixture.
Bake until bubbly, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for about 2 hours.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift the sugar and flour into a mixing bowl and beat in the butter.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Slowly pour in the buttermilk, then the vanilla, mixing well.
Pour the batter into the unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes or until the pie is golden and the custard has set. Cool to room temperature before serving.

title: arroz con pollo(puerto rican)
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces.
Mash in mortar the oregano leaves, peppercorns, garlic, salt, olive oil and vinegar; rub chicken with mixture.
Brown chicken lightly in 3 tablespoons oil. Reduce heat to moderate and add chopped ham, salt pork, onion, green pepper, chili pepper and cilantro, then add chopped green olives, capers and tomato.
Cook for 8 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and rice and cook 5 minutes.
Drain liquid from peas and add to kettle.
Save the peas for later.
Add boiling water, then mix and cook rapidly uncovered for 15 minutes until liquid is absorbed. With a large spoon turn rice from bottom to top.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes, then add peas and turn rice once more. Then cover and cook 5 minutes.
Garnish top with pimentos and serve at once.

title: scalloped tomatoes and cheese casserole
directions: Season tomatoes with salt, pepper and sugar.
Arrange alternate layers of tomatoes, bread crumbs and cheese in baking dish.
Dot top with butter.
Bake in moderate oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: delicious pumpkin pie
directions: Into large mixing bowl, place pumpkin, milk, eggs, vanilla and spices.
Blend well with mixer.
Pour into partially baked pie crust and bake at 375° until pie is firm in middle or inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool and serve with whipping cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain and
mix
with 1 package taco seasoning. Simmer as directed	on package.
Place meat mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and let cool.

title: egg rolls
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add pork and shrimp and saute about 5 minutes.
Add water chestnuts, carrots, cabbage and bean sprouts.
Cook until tender but firm. Season and set aside to cool.
Separate wrappers and add 2 tablespoons of the filling.
Wrap and roll.
Deep fry until brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt cheese in soup.
Alternate layers of soup mixture, eggs and asparagus.
Crumble crackers or onion rings.
Melt a little butter and pour over cracker crumbs.
Grease or spray pan.
Cook until it bubbles.

title: philly cheese steak
directions: *The only place I have found this is at Fino's on the Hill at McLean and Madison in Memphis.
It's worth the trip!

title: emily's favorite pancakes
directions: Dice peaches into bite size pieces; reserve liquid.
Mix pancake mix as instructed, substituting 1/2 of reserved liquid for 1/2 of milk needed for pancakes.
Add peaches to mix and cook pancakes in skillet.
Enjoy!

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all together by hand.
Pour into oiled 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: southern style quail
directions: Wash quail.
Pat dry and split each down the back.
Salt and pepper each quail half and coat with flour.
Heat oil in a covered skillet and brown quail on all sides.
Reduce heat to low and add light cream.
Cook 25 minutes or until quail is tender.
Serve with hot homemade biscuits.

title: raisin sauce(great for ham)
directions: In
medium pan mix the first 3 ingredients.
Slowly add the next
Stir
over
medium heat until fairly thick.
Add raisins and stir to heat through.

title: sticky buns
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Place frozen dough balls in Bundt pan.
Melt butter and pour over dough balls.
Mix nuts, pudding, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Pour over rolls.
Let sit out covered overnight to rise.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: nippy corned beef 'n cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley in large bowl and mix until thoroughly blended.
Shape into ball.
Wrap tightly in foil and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into small cubes or triangles.
Be sure all ingredients are cool.
Mix all ingredients; chill well before serving.

title: the "ashton" cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and cake flour.
Preheat oven to 325°. Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time, then mix in Presto flour and cake mix alternating with milk.
Check after adding milk to be sure you get the consistency of cake batter.
Pour into 10-cup Bundt pan.
Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes, checking after 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the butter, oil and brown sugar. Gradually add eggs and milk.
In a small bowl, combine salt, soda, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour.
Gradually mix the flour mixture and the molasses alternately to the egg mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with lemon rum sauce or whipped cream.

title: bobbie's lemon nut cake
directions: Soften butter and cream sugar together, add beaten eggs and lemon extract, mix thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together and add half to butter and sugar mixture.
Blend.
Add raisins and pecans to other half of dry ingredients.
Add everything and mix well.
Put in a greased tube pan.
Sit on top shelf and add pie pan of water on lower shelf.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Top with crushed corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber dunk
directions: Soften the cream cheese. Add the grated cucumber, onion and enough mayonnaise to soften. This can be served with chips or fresh vegetables.
Sprinkle paprika on top for garnish.

title: cocoa icing
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Beat for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs until light; add mayonnaise, salt and undiluted soup.
Blend well and add to broccoli.
Add cooked rice and grated cheese.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Spread over broccoli.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole no. 1
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo until clear.
Cook broccoli as directed and drain well.
Mix broccoli with soup, cheese, onion and celery.
Stir in cooked rice and mix.

title: glazed carrots with lemon and garlic
directions: Cut carrots into thin rounds and finely pare lemon rind. Place carrots in a wide saucepan with pared lemon rind, butter, sugar, garlic and seasonings. Add sufficient cold water to just cover.
Bring to a boil and cook over moderate heat for about 12 minutes until carrots are tender and liquid has evaporated, shaking pan occasionally to prevent sticking.
Serve garnished with dill and lemon rind.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Mix everthing except crackers and margarine.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with crushed crackers and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: breakfast brunch
directions: Toss together bread and cheese.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
Use a 9 x 13-inch greased glass dish.
Put cubed bread and cheese in dish.
Pour egg mixture over bread and cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and take out of refrigerator for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bacon, sausage or ham may be added.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix well with hands all except chips and paraffin.
Use large container.
Chill in bowl until cool.
Roll into balls.
Chill overnight.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip balls into chocolate with toothpick and place on wax paper or cookie sheet until dry.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken in a bag
directions: You will also need a 10 x 16-inch cooking bag.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in skillet until crisp. Remove pieces from skillet and drain.
Pour off drippings, reserving 2 tablespoons to return to skillet.
Blend in sugar, onion, flour and seasonings.
Gradually add water and vinegar. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Add potatoes and bacon pieces.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally 5 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Cook
onion and garlic in butter until tender.	Stir in rice until
thoroughly
coated.	Add parsley, salt, thyme and pepper; stir
well.
Combine
broth
and water in a saucepan. Bring
to
a boil
and	pour
over rice mixture.
Pour entire mixture then into a large rectangular baking dish.
Cover with foil
and
bake at	350°
for
minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mom's potato soup
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients and cook until tender. Mix together the milk and flour. Add to potato mixture and cook until thickened. Add the cheese. Cook until cheese melts.

title: 42's sauce
directions: Empty jelly into a pan.
Add equal amount of barbecue sauce (use empty jar to measure).
Cook over low heat until jelly has melted.

title: crown casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain fat off.
Add next 4 ingredients; bring to boil.
Put into casserole dish and top with biscuits.
Brush with mayonnaise.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: christmas odor punch
directions: Place dry ingredients in a jar or calico bag.
To mix, add dry ingredients to 1 quart water and simmer.
This fills kitchen with a wonderful aroma.

title: dipping batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
For fish, add 2 more teaspoons of vinegar.
Good for fresh vegetables and fish.

title: raw cucumber pickle
directions: Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Add salt and celery seed.
Pour over all other ingredients (cucumber, onion and peppers).
Will keep several weeks.

title: fish fried in beer batter
directions: Wash fish and pat dry.
Combine beer and biscuit mix.
Dip fish in batter.
Fry in enough oil to cover fish.
Turn when brown and fry on other side.
Amount depends on size and amount of fish.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble half of baked and cooled cake in punch bowl.
Top with half of the pie filling, half of the pudding, half of the pineapple, half of the bananas and half of the nondairy whipped topping.
Repeat layers using remaining half of each ingredient. Garnish with coconut, pecans and cherries.

title: lo-cal seafood newburg
directions: Combine 1/2 cup milk and flour.
Stir to a smooth paste.
Pour into top of double boiler; add remaining milk.
Heat until hot and thick.
Add Butter Buds, parsley, seasoning and shrimp.
Serve 1/4 of mixture over each slice of toast.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients, stir into creamed mixture. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of floured fork to make crisscrosses.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: poached salmon
directions: Simmer all of the ingredients for 5 minutes.
Place salmon fillets in the liquid, cover and simmer for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: spicy vegetable-cheese chili
directions: Heat oil in a large heavy pot.
Add celery, green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook covered until vegetables are tender.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake as you would cornbread.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Put sugar and cocoa in microwave-safe bowl; make a hole for milk.
Pour in milk and place stick of butter in center of dish. Microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Margarine may not be completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter until blended stiff. Pour on 2 flat dinner plates, about 1-inch to 1 1/2-inches thick. Put in icebox for 20 minutes to cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Mix all together.
Place 4 to 6 (1 1/2-inch) chops in a Ziploc or dish including the mixture and marinate overnight in the fridge.

title: homemade onion soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in airtight container. About 5 tablespoons of mix are equal to 1 (1.25 oz.) package soup mix.

title: baked salmon
directions: Clean and wash fish.
Place in foil lined pan.
Put onion, lemon slices, parsley and garlic cloves in the stomach cavity. Salt and pepper outside of fish.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until the fish is tender.

title: tropical fruit jam
directions: Measure sugar and set aside.
Put all fruit in a bowl and mix well.
Put in heavy saucepan.
Put on high heat.
Add one box of Sure-Jell and bring to a hard rolling boil.
Add sugar all at once and bring back to a hard rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Skim off the foam and ladle into jars.
Seal with hot lids and turn upside down for 1/2 hour.

title: green chili chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Boil chicken. Let cool, then shred. Save the broth. Saute onion in margarine until slightly soft. Combine onion with soups, green chili and chicken broth. Tear 6 tortillas into small pieces and cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread 1/2 of the shredded chicken over the tortillas. Then spread 1/2 of the sauce mixture over the chicken and top with cheese. Repeat the layers, ending with cheese on top. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until very hot and bubbly and slightly browned.

title: cranberry wassail
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pour over ice cubes.

title: health salad
directions: Use mayonnaise thinned with milk or use sour cream.
Mix well and serve.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, Parmesan cheese, eggs and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Combine tomato sauce and oregano.
Pour mixture over meat loaf.
Top meat loaf with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Continue baking 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend well. Makes 2 servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Then mix flour and baking powder (sift).
Add this to pulp mixture.
Add melted margarine and buttermilk.
Pour into shallow, greased pan and bake in 375° oven.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and green pepper.
Mix together with soup, water and slightly thawed vegetables.
Place in 2 1/2-quart size casserole dish and top with evenly placed Tater Tots.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Drop in egg yolks.
Add bananas. Add dry ingredients and milk.
Add beaten egg whites last.
Pour into loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 300° until top springs back when pressed gently.

title: stir and roll pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine 2 cups baking mix, milk and cheese with a wooden spoon until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown. Combine butter or margarine, melted, and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm. Makes 10 to 12.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In bowl, stir water into gelatin until dissolved; transfer to 8-cup serving bowl.
Stir in strawberries, raspberries, cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Refrigerate until completely set, 4 hours. In bowl with mixer on high speed, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping. If desired, transfer to pastry bag fitted with large star tip.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain and squeeze out all excess water.
Cool in refrigerator.
When cooled, mix all other ingredients together.
Refrigerate dip for several hours.

title: never fail cornbread
directions: Melt butter or margarine in Corning Ware baking dish.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt.
Add buttermilk and melted butter.
Mix well and return to pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: christmas bars
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix flour and sugar with fruit and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Cut into bars.

title: creamy frozen fruit cups
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Halve 9 cherries. Chop the remaining cherries.
Set aside halved cherries and 18 oranges for garnish.
Add pineapple, pecans and chopped cherries to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in whipped topping and remaining oranges.
Line muffin cups with liners.
Spoon fruit mixture into cups.
Garnish with cherries and oranges.
Freeze until firm. Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: kourabiedes (greek cookies)
directions: Cream butter until very light (20 to 30 minutes).
Beat in sugar, egg yolks, almonds, brandy and orange juice.
Sift baking powder with flour and carefully blend into butter mixture.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Combine the ingredients in saucepan. Boil rapidly on medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 260°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda; immediately pour over 6 quarts of popped corn.
Coat corn.
Pour in buttered pan.
Bake for 1 hour; stir 3 or 4 times to break corn apart.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely and store in tightly covered container.
(If sticky, put in oven for a little while until crisp.)

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in Dutch oven until beef is browned.
Drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, basil, salt and pepper and tomatoes (with liquid).
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer (stirring occasionally) for 10 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and Veg-All (with liquid).
Cover and cook until macaroni is tender, 10 to 15 minutes or longer.

title: egg casserole
directions: In greased pan, sprinkle croutons over bottom, then sprinkle cheese over croutons.
Pour eggs over all.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine together until smooth. Add sugar; mix well. Add vanilla and beat until smooth. Spread on cooled cake. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: apple caramel nut pie
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl; stir well.
Pour in pie shell and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; boil 5 minutes.
Chill in refrigerator.
It will thicken.
Wash and slice berries.
Mix berries with thickened mixture; pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Thaw fish and shrimp, if frozen.
Cut fish into 1 inch pieces.
In large saucepan, combine broth, mushrooms, carrot, onion, garlic, marjoram, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in sauce, tomatoes, fish and shrimp. Return to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 2 or 3 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Discard bay leaf. Sprinkle with parsley and lemon peel.
Serves 4 generously.

title: oriental chicken in puff pastry
directions: Prepare puffed pastry according to box.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain and cut up; set aside.
Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan and stir in baking mix, ginger and garlic.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in broth and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute; reduce heat.
Stir in broccoli and remaining ingredients. Heat through.
Fill puff pastries with chicken mixture. Serve with a side dish of rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat. When melted, add sugar.
Allow to cool slightly, then add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Add salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Add nuts or chips, if desired.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour cherry mixture in dish.
Crumble dry cake mix directly from box over cherry mixture. Slice margarine over mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake approximately 50 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: ice cream pie(serves 10)
directions: Combine and cook over low heat until all melted and thickened the first 5 ingredients.
Cool to room temperature.
Line pie pan with vanilla wafers.
Put ice cream into pie pan in chunks, alternating with sauce.
Freeze immediately.
Cut in small pieces as this pie is rich.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix well, dip for any type of vegetables.

title: italian style chicken
directions: Put chicken parts in pan.
Put potatoes, cut in fourths, on top of chicken.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, parsley and lots of grated Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle a little bit of oil on chicken and water.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in a large mixer bowl for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve coffee granules in hot water; combine with buttermilk.
Combine flour and cocoa; add alternately with buttermilk mixture, beating just until blended.
Pour in 12 cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 20 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely; frost with Cocoa Fudge Frosting.

title: beef and cabbage
directions: Brown ground beef in a large pot. Add onion and garlic and continue to brown beef. Break into small pieces. Drain fat and return pot to medium heat. Add tomato sauce, applesauce, vinegar, brown sugar, thyme, salt and pepper. Mix well and bring to a boil while stirring constantly. Add cabbage, then reduce heat and cover pot. Simmer while covered about 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook until cabbage is tender. Cook with lid off for a few minutes to thicken the sauce if you would like.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and water; let stand for 15 minutes.
Strain off water.
Mix 2 cups of the mixture with 4 cups sugar.
Boil 15 minutes and let stand 3 days.
Stir once each day.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sunny day salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise. Chill for 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Add flour, vinegar, water and sugar to onion and bacon grease. Stir and cook until mixture thickens.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix gently and top with sliced eggs.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots (do not overcook).
Drain and cool.
Cut onions and green pepper in round slices, then mix with carrots.
Mix all other ingredients together, then pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours or longer.
Drain to serve.
This will keep for two weeks in refrigerator.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: turtles
directions: Melt the caramels and water in double boiler.
Add the pecans and stir until mixed well.
Drop by small clusters on waxed paper. Freeze until hard.
Melt the Hershey bars and paraffin.
Dip the clusters in the chocolate and place on waxed paper until set. (Hint:
Toothpick makes a good dipper.)
Yield:

title: batter for vegetables
directions: Place all ingredients in small bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Use for onion rings, zucchini, cauliflower or other vegetables.
Coat with batter.
Fry in deer fat 2 minutes or until golden brown. Drain and serve hot.

title: hominy salad
directions: Rinse hominy and drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients and chill well.
Add the cheese right before it is served.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Place batter in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 2 cups fruit.
Pour fruit juice on top. Sprinkle evenly 3/4 cup sugar on top.
Pour hot water over all. Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: chicken liver canapes
directions: Place a piece of chicken liver and a slice of water chestnut on each half strip of bacon.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Drain on paper towel; serve hot.

title: mystery spread
directions: Cut bacon into thin strips.
Mix Tabasco, mustard and mayonnaise together; blend with cheese, bacon and onion.
Roll into small rolls.
Place on wax paper and chill.

title: sugar plum cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam or oil good and coat pan with sugar generously.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 20 minutes in pan, then onto cake plate.

title: butter and cream chicken
directions: Dip chicken in water and coat with seasonings mixed in flour. Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix water and powdered milk.
Pour over chicken and bake for 65 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle on cheese and bake just until melted.

title: stuffed gooseneck squash
directions: Cook squash in salt water until tender, but not soft.
Remove water and cool.
Split squash lengthwise.
Scoop out squash pulp and reserve.
Place margarine, onion and contents of seasoning packet in large skillet.
Cook until onions are clear but not brown.
Add stuffing crumbs.
Mash squash pulp.
Add to stuffing mixture.
Add sage, salt and pepper.
Mix until crumbs are soft. Add more chicken broth if needed.
tags: Stove Top corn bread stuffing mix

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Put 1/2 in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour squash into dish and top with remaining stuffing. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Keeps well!

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients with vinegar.
Blend or shake this mixture with oil.
Makes 3 cups.

title: refrigerator raisin bran muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl. Stir in cereal.
Mix butter, oil and eggs together and blend into dry ingredients.
Do not stir batter again.
Store batter covered in a nonmetallic bowl in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
As needed, fill lightly greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine the flour and sugar, set aside.
In a small pan place butter, water and cocoa, bring to a boil.
Stir in the flour and sugar and mix well.
Add the eggs, baking soda, buttermilk and vanilla, mix well then pour into an 11 x 17 x 2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400°f. 200°c. gas mark 6 for 20 minutes.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: In large saucepan, blanche cabbage in boiling, salted water 3 minutes.
Drain and refresh cabbage under cold, running water; drain well.
In saucepan, saute onion in butter until it's soft; add cabbage and toss mixture well.
Add cream cheese; cook over low heat, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add dill, salt and pepper.
Simmer 3 minutes.

title: english crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients in blender and mix until smooth.
Place flaked crabmeat (canned, fresh or frozen) in buttered casserole dish.
Add the mixture to casserole and stir in thoroughly.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cabbage lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and pepper until meat is brown.
Boil cabbage until tender.
Save 2 cups of liquid from cabbage and drain off excess.
Combine reserved liquid, oregano, salt, pepper and tomato paste.
Simmer over low heat for 4 minutes.
Add meat mixture to tomato liquid.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer cabbage, then tomato mixture.
Repeat layer.
Top with slices of cheese. Bake at 400° until cheese is browned, about 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until warm. Good on chicken, beef and pork!

title: beer rocks
directions: First, shred cabbage and place in a
large pan; chop onion and add cabbage.
Pour in beer and water and cook until cabbage is tender.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together and then add vanilla and 2 eggs. Beat well and add flour, then nuts.
Spread in an oblong pan that has been greased and sprinkled with flour.
Spread 1 package of chocolate chips on top and bake in a 325° oven for about 30 or 40 minutes.

title: two minute fudge in microwave
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla until blended.
Top with butter.
Microwave at High (10) for 2 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Stir in the nuts (optional), and pour into waxed paper-lined 8-inch square dish.
Chill.

title: mexican style pasta salad
directions: Cook shells.
Rinse and drain.
Mix in a large mixing bowl. Combine all ingredients except spices and mix thoroughly and then add spices to taste.
Feel free to add your favorite veggies and serve with corn bread or garlic bread.

title: skyline apple muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar, oil and egg.
In another bowl, combine flour, salt and soda, mixing well.
Add the flour mixture to the sugar mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Mix well after each addition.
Fold in the apples and nuts.
Pour into muffin pans that have been sprayed with Pam.

title: she crab soup
directions: Bring entire mixture to a slow boil.
Cook slowly to avoid sticking.
Just before serving, add 1/4 cup sherry.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend well.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quickie peach cobbler
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar and oleo.
Break or slice toast in strips and blend in egg mixture.
Pour peaches and juice in bottom of shallow pan.
Pour egg mixture over peaches and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is brown and crisp.
Serve with whipped topping and/or ice cream.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook ground beef until brown, then drain off excess oil.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and undrained mushrooms; mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes or until onions are soft.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients. Put in casserole.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
May be made a day ahead, refrigerated, then baked when needed.
Freezes well also.

title: brown sugar drop cookies
directions: In a small bowl beat egg until light and fluffy (on high speed).
Add sugar and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Blend in walnuts.

title: hawaiian bread sub
directions: Slice Hawaiian bread in 5 layers horizontally.
Layer each section with deli meat and spread each layer with mustard, mayonnaise mixture.
Slice to serve from top to bottom.

title: beef macaroni casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix together the macaroni, green pepper, cheese, mustard and mayonnaise.
Spread this mixture in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Spread dry mixture on top with the bread crumbs or cracker crumbs and the melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Ovens may vary; may take longer in some.

title: skinny dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine dry mustard, minced onion and water. Set aside for a few minutes to develop the flavor and rehydrate the mustard and onion.
Meanwhile, mix together the rest of the ingredients.
Stir in onion and mustard mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with vegetable relishes and/or crackers. Makes 1 cup.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great dish for large gathering.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a round cake pan.
In a large bowl, sift together the dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins.
In another bowl, combine eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Add to the dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Bake 1 hour or until top is lightly browned.
Let cool on rack before slicing.
Serve with butter.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Next morning, cover with 1/2 pound shredded cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: jiffy rhubarb dessert
