directions: Grease a 7 x 10-inch pan.
Put the raw rhubarb in the pan and sprinkle with the sugar and gelatin, the the cake mix.
Gently pour the water over the whole thing, and dribble butter over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone.
Mix broth, milk, soup and onion.
Put layer of dressing, chicken and liquid.
Add another layer of dressing.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water to cover 8 to 10 minutes. Drain.
Set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add flour, salt, mustard and pepper, stirring until blended.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cheese and carrots.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine breadcrumbs, melted butter and parsley.
Sprinkle over carrot mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seafood alfredo
directions: Cool pasta, according to directions.
Meanwhile, in large skillet, saute garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in crab, shrimp, lemon juice and pepper.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add Alfredo sauce and peas.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Drain pasta. Top with seafood mixture and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: coconut ring cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° and grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan. Beat all ingredients, except coconut and powdered sugar, in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping sides frequently.
Beat on medium speed 4 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes then remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Put in mixer bowl the soft oleo, powdered sugar and 1 cup sugar.
Add the salad oil, then the eggs.
Continue beating while adding eggs.
Add the plain flour, baking soda, salt, vanilla and lemon extract (optional).
Let stand in refrigerator until firm or overnight.
Drop from teaspoon;
flatten with a sugary fork. Sprinkle on colored sugar and/or sprinkles.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 80.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with bread or crackers.
Make 2 hours before serving.

title: garden soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve hot.

title: blueberry glaze pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon in a medium saucepan.
Mix well.
Stir in butter, lemon juice and 2 cups of blueberries.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently to mash a few berries.
Boil 1 or 2 minutes until margarine melts and sugar dissolves.
Cool completely.
Fold in remaining 2 cups berries. Pour into crust.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and Karo; cook with candy thermometer to 255° or hard-ball stage. Pour mixture over beaten egg whites, beating continually, until candy loses its gloss, adding the vanilla and nuts. (Add vanilla and nuts before the candy loses gloss.) Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Makes over 100 pieces.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons melted butter until smooth.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles and spread.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture into center of triangle.
Pull 3 corners of dough to top center.
Twist and seal.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with crushed croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: red velvet cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan. In large bowl, beat butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla, beating well. Stir together flour, cocoa and salt. Add alternately to butter mixture with buttermilk mixture, mixing well. Stir in baking soda and vinegar. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Frost.

title: chocolate graham cracker surprise
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, then add 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Layer cake as follows:
graham crackers, pudding/Cool Whip mixture.
Repeat layers until pan is full, ending with graham crackers.

title: meat loaf vegetable
directions: Mix together all ingredients and shape into a loaf.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Yields 10 servings.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter. Add broccoli and cook for a few minutes until broccoli is tender. Add garlic cheese and let it melt. Add cream of mushroom and celery soups. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook on low until hot. Serve with chips.

title: pickle relish
directions: Grind coarse. Let stand for 2 hours, drain and make syrup.

title: lady locks
directions: Mix well.
Cover with waxed paper for 3 hours or overnight. Roll on lightly floured board about 1/4-inch thick.
(If too thin, the strips will break.)
Cut strips 1/2-inch wide and 7-inches long.
Wrap on foil covered clothespins.
Grease cookie sheets and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Remove clothespins while cookies are hot.
Fill with filling of your choice.
Gob Filling works best.
You can also tint icing for special occasions.
I also roll them in powdered sugar.

title: baked yellow squash casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Blanch squash slices in large pot of salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and place in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and reserve 1/3 cup. Combine the remaining crumb mixture with scallions, eggs, salt, pepper, sugar and cheese.
Stir this into squash slices.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until golden brown and a knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: cheese roll
directions: Let cheese reach room temperature.
Mix together all ingredients except paprika.
Form into two long rolls.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill before serving.
Slice and serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Pour 1 cup pecan halves on top and push down with fingers. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until done.

title: chicken dinner pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry or use large pie crust. Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat, stir in broth and cream. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Fill and arrange crisscross lattice top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: christmas cake cookies
directions: Remove the pits from dates and cut into chunks; cut candied cherries in quarters.
Slice pineapple into thin slivers.
Blanch almonds; coarsely chop them and toast until golden.
Chop Brazil nuts.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Work butter until soft and creamy, gradually add the sugar and continue working mixture until quite smooth.
Beat in eggs, then stir in sifted flour mixture and add all fruits and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake 10 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.
Don't overbake as cookies are nicer when softer in texture.
Remove from oven, cool slightly and remove from cookie sheets.
Yields 150 to 170 cookies.

title: soldier's fudge
directions: Butter baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Heat milk, chocolate chips and unsweetened chocolate in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread mixture evenly in pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cream with electric mixer. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; beat for 2 minutes.
Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour into 1 large greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Test, when knife inserted comes out clean, cake is done. Do not overbake.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually add to blended mixture, mixing after each addition until smooth.
Add chocolate chips and stir into batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: flank steak with whiskey sauce(low-fat)
directions: In medium glass or stainless steel bowl, combine teriyaki sauce, 1 1/2 teaspoons garlic, the vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Add steak; turn several times to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 30 minutes.

title: never fail caramels
directions: In a large sauce pan, mix all ingredients.

Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly to a soft ball or slightly higher; should be bubbling and turn slightly darker and clearer when done. Pour out on large cookie sheet; sprinkle nuts on top if desired. Let cool.	Cut and wrap in wax paper.

title: turkey or chicken salad
directions: Remove meat from bones and cut into bite-size pieces.
Add chopped celery and onion.
Mix with mayonnaise and salt to taste. Chill at least one hour.
Suitable for salad or sandwich spread.

title: poke sallet
directions: Fill pan with tender poke greens; add 2 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Drain and add another cup of water.
Cook on low heat about 10 minutes; drain well.
Add butter and cream cheese; stir.
Add eggs and stir.
Cook in same pan until eggs are cooked. Season to taste with salt.

title: tortilla chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes uncovered.
Cover and bake another 1/2 hour in foil in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Use 12-inch skillet.
Cook meat in butter until it loses its red color.
Sprinkle half of spaghetti sauce mix over meat and mix.
Spoon cottage cheese over meat.
Top with noodles in a layer and sprinkle with rest of spaghetti sauce mix, basil, parsley flakes and salt.
Pour chopped tomatoes, tomato sauce and 1 cup of water over the top.
Make sure all is covered and moistened. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 35 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese all over top and let stand 5 minutes or until melted.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar.
Melt margarine and bring to a boil.
Remove form heat and stir in sour cream and remainder of sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and beaten egg.
Mix well.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to yeast mixture.
Mix.
Refrigerate overnight or longer.
Form into rolls and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake until brown at 375° (about 15 minutes).

title: baby bear stew
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add rest of ingredients except kidney beans.
Simmer for 1 hour or more.
Add beans 1/2 hour before serving so they will not overcook.
Serve as is or over rice. This is an excellent and delicious way to get your "baby bears" to eat vegetables.

title: margie's apple pie
directions: Put apples in pie crust.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread mixture on top of apples.
Bake at 350° until crust is done.

title: apple crumb cake(serves 16)
directions: Blend sugar, margarine and eggs in bowl with spoon.
Stir in graham crumbs, apple and walnuts until blended.
Spread batter into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm to the touch.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.
Prep time:
20 minutes.
Total time:
2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a saucepan heat butter, chicken soup, mushroom soup and mushrooms together until butter is melted.
Stir often.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle the dry Minute rice on top.
Place cleaned chicken pieces on top of rice.
Sprinkle the dry Lipton onion soup mix over the top of the chicken.
Cover well with foil. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Quick to make.
Delicious!

title: shrimp siciliana
directions: In a medium bowl, combine bread crumbs and milk.
With a fork, beat in the eggs, Tabasco and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 45 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy 3-quart saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes or until a candy thermometer reaches 234°.
Remove from heat and add chocolate morsels.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until chocolate melts; stir in peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased wax paper; cool and store in an airtight container.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: tresa's pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into 2-inch cubes.
Put steak and water in roast pan.
Cook in oven on 450° until steak is almost done.
Add sliced bell pepper and sliced onion to meat.
Cook until peppers and onions are soft.
Serve hot.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix dressing with cream cheese; stir well until smooth.
Chop green onions, green peppers, black olives and celery.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over 6 to 8 tortillas, then sprinkle vegetables over each tortilla.
Roll each tortilla up and chill.
Slice into 1/2-inch to 1-inch slices and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
This makes a big salad.
Everything is optional and other fruit can be added, but you must
use the strawberries and condensed milk.
This also freezes like a dream.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: brown sugar banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add the eggs; mix well. Stir in flour, soda and salt; mix thoroughly, then add bananas and vanilla extract and nuts if desired.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for one hour.
Store in aluminum foil after cooling.

title: grandma wall's christmas cookies
directions: Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll out on floured pastry sheet and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes for soft cookies.

title: izala's meat loaf
directions: Mix all together;
place
in
baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup tomatoes on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ground beef surprise
directions: Cook macaroni as to directions.
Brown onion in oil.
Add meat.
Cook until lightly browned.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except macaroni, parsley and cheese.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until celery and peppers are tender.
Stir in macaroni and cook 10 minutes longer.
Garnish with parsley and cheese.

title: roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese and with electric mixer, beat in Hidden Valley dressing packet.
Spread on shells (like you would butter bread); sprinkle olives, peppers and scallions on each shell.
Roll up tight; put in plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: banana split dessert pizza
directions: Preheat
oven
In medium mixing bowl, combine sweetened
condensed milk, sour cream, 1/4 cup lemon juice and vanilla; mix well.
Chill.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook peppers 5 minutes in boiling water to cover.
Drain and set aside.
In frying pan, brown ground chuck with celery and onion, stirring occasionally.
Add rice, stewed tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Mix well and spoon mixture into peppers.
Place peppers in shallow pan.
Combine tomato sauce and sugar.
Mix well.
Spoon half of sauce over peppers.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Spoon remaining sauce during last 5 minutes of baking.

title: banana, nut & chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening & sugar. Add egg - beat. Add bananas & nuts. Then add oats and chocolate chips. Sift flour with soda, salt, nutmeg, and cinnamon, and gradually add to shortening mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet, set 1 inch apart. Bake in 400° oven for 10-12 minutes.

title: mom johnson's noodles
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Make a round hole in middle of flour. Put in whole eggs and egg yolks.
Mix well with fork.
Then start adding flour until you can roll them out.

title: corn-rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to instructions of package.
Add butter, stir until melted.
Add corn and soup.
Grate 1 cup or more of sharp cheese.
Combine with mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle some cheese on top and paprika (for color).

title: spiced watermelon rind(mildred gregory)
directions: Remove all green outer covering and all pink from rind before cutting into shapes.
There should be 2 quarts.
Cover rind shapes with cold water in a large kettle (porcelainized iron or enamel ware).
Bring water to a boil and cook 10 to 20 minutes or until tender crisp and rind can be pierced with a fork.
Stir in alum; remove from heat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, drain; add sugar and vinegar.
Tie spices in cheesecloth and add. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat; cool.
Cover and refrigerate again overnight.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break cake into crumbs in large mixing bowl.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water and place frozen strawberries in Jell-O. Put in refrigerator until it's at the jellied stage.
Mix in bowl with whipped cream.
Place in pan greased with oil (Wesson) for 24 hours.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Mix the cream of mushroom soup with the milk, salt and pepper. Add the ham, potatoes and onions to the soup mixture.
Stir together well and spoon into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish or casserole.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: pancit(pon-ceet; from the philippines)
directions: You will need 1 large pot and 1 large skillet.

title: 3 week cole slaw
directions: Combine all chopped vegetables in large bowl.
Set aside.
Cook the sugar, oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt until mixture boils. Pour over cabbage mixture, cover tightly and store in refrigerator for three days before serving.
Will keep one month in refrigerator.

title: low-fat chocolate cake
directions: Cook 65 minutes in Bundt pan at 350°.
Grease and flour pan well.
Wait a long time until cool.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind all vegetables.
Mix and boil 2 minutes.
Add vegetables and boil until changes color.
Can in approximately 8 pints.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage in skillet; drain well.
Butter bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and line with biscuits, firmly pressing to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients, beat well and pour over sausage and cheese. Bake at 425° for 15 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until well blended and smooth. Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.
Use to dip cookies, cake cubes, fresh fruit, pretzel sticks, etc. Makes 2 cups.

title: midge logan's sticky buns
directions: Cut bread dough into 12 pieces.
Place in bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Place remaining ingredients on dough in order given. Let stand overnight on counter to raise.
Then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn upside-down on serving plate as soon as it comes from the oven.

title: richmond chocolate frosting
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water and cook until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla.
Spread on cake while hot.
Frosts an 8 or 9-inch cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar and add beaten eggs, flour, salt, vanilla and Karo syrup.
Stir well.
Place pecans in the bottoms of the pie shells and pour the mixture over, dividing evenly. Bake until firm 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mediterranean turkey sandwiches
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat over medium-high heat about 30 seconds.
Add ground turkey, bell pepper and onion; cook about 3 to 5 minutes, stirring until turkey is lightly browned.
Add 1/4 cup water, garlic powder, oregano and pepper.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, or until water is absorbed.
In a small bowl, blend yogurt and lemon juice.
Fill each pocket bread half with meat mixture.
Add yogurt mixture.
Yields 5 servings.

title: andrew's fudgies
directions: Beat all ingredients (except chocolate bits and nuts) very well; it will be very thin.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate bits and chopped nuts over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 35 to 40 minutes in pan.

title: sand tarts
directions: Combine all ingredients, except powdered sugar; mix well. Roll into balls, then press with floured fork to flatten. (Cookies do not increase in size during baking time.)
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or light brown.
Cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.
"A Christmas favorite at our house."

title: spanish rice
directions: Grind pepper and onion.
Cook meat, onion, pepper and Minute rice in frying pan about 5 minutes.
Add tomato juice.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with layer of cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together well, pour into pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: angel pie
directions: Stir all together.
Do not beat.
Pour into the pie shells and chill until ready to serve.

title: meatloaf
directions: Grind onion and bread together, then put oatmeal through grinder.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a loaf pan (pyrex works best).
Bake at 400 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Best if mixed up ahead of time and refrigerated 24 hours before baking.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in 1 3/4 cups water for 5 minutes.
In 1/4 cup water, mix brown sugar and cloves.
Combine this mixture with the raisins and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Pour into 2 small or 1 large pie shell and bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Wash rice and spread in bottom of casserole.
Brown pork chops and place on top of rice.
Mix soup mix, water and bouillon.
Pour over rice.
Bake, covered, 40 minutes at 350°.

title: green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into buttered shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat out the cookie dough on greased cookie sheet and bake according to instructions on package. Cool.
Mix the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar and spread over cookie crust.
Cover with glaze made from 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick, then add 3 tablespoons strawberry Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Slice the bananas over the cream cheese. Cover the bananas with the glaze. Add the peaches, strawberries, pineapple and blueberries. Chill and slice.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half the batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, mix the caramels, margarine and milk.
Melt over low heat.
Pour caramel mixture over cake layer. Sprinkle with peanuts and chocolate chips.
Spread remaining batter over cake and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange swizzle punch
directions: Put orange juice concentrate into bowl.
Measure 5 cups ginger ale into bowl.
Add sherbet.
Slice 3 slices from the center of a fresh orange.
Use with cherries to garnish punch.

title: shredded yams
directions: Shred yams into one gallon water with salt added.
Combine sugar, syrup and 1/4 cup water in heavy saucepan.
Cook until it forms like syrup.
Drain potatoes.
Place in heat resistant 12 x 6 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Pour pineapple juice over potatoes, then the cooked syrup.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 35 minutes or until potatoes are translucent.

title: racy red punch
directions: Heat 1 cup of juice with red hots.
Stir until dissolved. Combine rest of juice and sugar.
Add cooled red hot mixture and chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Make well and add milk, oil and eggs.
Beat well by hand.
Add raisins, cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can keep batter in refrigerator up to 6 days.

title: round house chili
directions: Brown meat in cast-iron pot; drain off liquid (fat) and discard.
Mix all other ingredients in another pot, then add to meat pot and simmer for 4 hours.
Add beans just prior to final heating and serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding hot milk last.
Pour into well-greased 6 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven. Serve hot.
Yields 8 servings.

title: stove top roast beef
directions: Braise roast in Crisco in iron skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons water after beef roast is braised.
Remove roast before making brown gravy from water and brownings left in the skillet.
Put 4 cups water in Dutch oven on top of stove.
Pour gravy from water and beef brownings.
Put in potatoes and carrots and cook low on top of stove.
Put in pickle juice to tender.

title: break-a-way bread
directions: Pour boiling water over Crisco and set aside to melt.
Pour warm water over the yeast and let dissolve.
Beat eggs with fork and add to cooled waters.
Add sugar, salt and flour; mix well. Cover in large bowl to rise overnight.
Roll out on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted margarine and stack in 2 Bundt pans.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake until brown at 400° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: toasted coconut cream pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spread coconut in a rimmed baking sheet. Bake (toss twice) 10 to 15 minutes, until toasted. Let cool. Mix pudding and 1 1/2 cups toasted coconut in a bowl; spread evenly in crust. Cover with reserved lid and chill 1 hour or up to 2 days.

title: cherry topped cheese pie
directions: Pie Crust: Combine graham crackers (crumbs) and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix in melted butter. Press firmly on bottom of pie pan. Chill 1 hour before filling.

title: aunt lucy's chili
directions: Brown onion, garlic and ground beef.
Drain off grease.
Add soup, beans and chili seasoning.
Cover and simmer.
Stir occasionally.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pie crust
directions: Melt 1/2 cup shortening; add 1/4 cup water and toss with flour.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: quick microwave bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a square dish; press evenly. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, until bubbly.
Let stand to cool.
In glass measuring cup, melt chocolate and peanut butter; spread on top.

title: herbed barbecue chicken
directions: Mix dressing according to package directions, except add 1/4 cup water, instead of only 2 tablespoons.
Get charcoal ready to medium-high heat.
Put 1 whole head of garlic into fire.
Brown chicken on outside, then wrap in heavy-duty foil after pouring dressing over chicken.
Continue cooking until chicken is well done.
After fully cooked, poke holes in bottom of foil and let drain.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, meal and milk.
Put margarine on top of corn.
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Sift together mace, salt and flour.
Mix cream mixture together with milk and vanilla.
Alternately add flour mixture to cream/milk mixture.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven for entire time.

title: party pizza
directions: Brown meat, then mix ingredients.
Place sauce on rye bread. Freeze.
Set oven for 400°; bake straight from the freezer for 15 minutes.

title: sausage egg breakfast
directions: Place croutons in 9 x 13 inch greased dish.
Top with cheese and browned sausage.
Beat eggs with mustard and 2 1/2 cup milk. Pour over and refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Add sugar.
Great with chicken, turkey, pork, etc.

title: tomatoes piquant
directions: Remove skins from tomatoes by placing them, one at a time, in boiling water to cover for about 30 to 35 seconds. (The skin will peel off easily.) Slice the tomatoes about 1/2-inch thick. Place tomatoes in a deep bowl. In a jar, combine the remaining ingredients. Shake well and pour dressing over the tomatoes. Cover and chill about 5 or 6 hours, spooning dressing over the tomatoes occasionally. At serving time, drain off dressing and snip more parsley over tomatoes for garnish. Sliced cucumbers are good with the tomatoes. Serves 6. Must do ahead.

title: sugar cookie recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar, salt and butter thoroughly.
Beat egg, lemon rind and vanilla into creamed mixture until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking powder. Stir into creamed mixture gradually.
Roll a small amount of dough at a time into 1/8-inch thick.
Put on floured board.
Cut dough with floured cookie cutters.
Transfer cookies to ungreased cookie sheets.
Brush cookie tops with egg whites and decorate with toppings.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes or until edges are brown.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cabbage crunch salad
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl and set aside.

title: italian meatball sandwiches
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, heat the oil over medium heat until hot.
Cook and stir the pepper strips and onion wedges 3 to 4 minutes or until tender.
Reduce heat to medium-low; add cooked meatballs and spaghetti sauce.
Cover and cook 5 to 6 minutes to heat through, stirring occasionally. Spoon equal amounts into the rolls.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Into one bowl, sift together sugar and other dry ingredients. Whip the cream until stiff; add eggs one at a time and continue whipping.
Add vanilla.
Fold dry ingredients into cream mixture. Mix two minutes.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans and bake in 425° oven until done, about 25 minutes.
Makes two small layers.
Double the recipe for three large layers.

title: ground beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Put ground beef and onion into a heavy pot or Dutch oven. Brown over medium heat, stirring.
Add celery, carrots, parsnip and cabbage.
Cook until meat is no longer pink and vegetables have begun to get tender, about 5 minutes.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Press into a 9-inch pie plate. Bake pie crust at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.

title: tomato and onion marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place meat of choice in a glass or Pyrex dish.
Coat meat with marinade, cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours (overnight if possible).

title: macadamia nut pie
directions: Mix molasses with hot water, blending well.
Mix flour, sugar and
soda.
Cut
in
butter to form coarse crumbs.
Line pie dish with
pastry.
Pour in 1/3 of molasses mixture.
Top with
crumb mixture.
Repeat,
adding
alternate
layers with crumbs on top. Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: judy's zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large bowl; stir in raisins and nuts.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in flour mixture until smooth.
Pour mixture into greased pan or pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 minutes, or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertips.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Start with rice or potatoes on bottom.
Cover with 1/2 can tomato sauce, then a layer of onion and bell pepper, mixed. Cover with 1/2 can tomato sauce, then a layer of kernel corn. Cover with 1/2 can tomato sauce and layer of ground beef.
Cover with 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix well and press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: baked dinner
directions: Put beef in dish.
Pour soups over beef, mix and cover.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours or bake in crock-pot.
Serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: waldorf chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple, but save juice.
Combine pineapple, chicken breasts, red apple, green apple, walnuts and celery.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: You will need a cookie press.

title: mo-mo's poke sallet
directions: Cut young and tender green poke sallet leaves in spring of year.
Parboil until tender.
Drain in colander and rinse twice with cold water.
Fry several strips of bacon and remove from frypan to drain.
Chop medium onion and saute in bacon grease. Add greens and stir until heated throughout.
Salt to taste. Slice 2 or 3 hard-boiled eggs on top of greens in serving dish.

title: kathy's crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients except crab meat.
Then add crab meat. Chill before serving.

title: pot roast barbecue style
directions: Combine onion, garlic, bouillon, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat in a large bowl.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Heat shortening in heavy skillet, remove meat from marinade and brown on both sides in hot fat.
Blend catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire and mustard into marinade and pour over meat.
Cover pan and simmer until meat is tender, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Gravy may be thickened slightly.

title: strawberry-grapefruit drink
directions: Break up strawberries, place berries and one cup grapefruit juice in blender. Cover and blend on high speed about 40 seconds. Add remaining juice. Blend until mixed. Serve over ice.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese and cracker crumbs.
Put a layer of mixture in bottom of casserole.
Put a a layer of asparagus with egg and celery on top of it.
Repeat until all is used. Pour mushroom soup with liquid of asparagus over all and sprinkle with potato chips crushed.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dressing for fresh fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over fruit.
Suggested fruits are grapes, watermelon, cantaloupe, bananas, pineapple and apples.

title: easy kool-aid pie
directions: Mix milk and Kool-Aid.
Pour into crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Place sliced biscuits in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle with additional cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve with sauce.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar.
(Mix 1 cup chopped nuts with brown sugar, if desired.)
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water 45 minutes to 1 hour. Let cool. Peel and mash. Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter. Beat at medium speed until smooth. Spoon into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: window cleaner
directions: Put mixture in a gallon jug.
Fill with water.

title: smoky salmon spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice, horseradish, onion, salt, pepper and liquid smoke.
Drain salmon; remove skin and bones. Flake the salmon with two forks.
Stir salmon into cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate at least one hour.
Shape into a roll. Sprinkle parsley over salmon, then roll into plastic or foil wrap. Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.

title: spinach-potato casserole
directions: Cook spinach, drain and set aside.
Mix next 4 ingredients. Add to this boiling water and cold milk.
Beat well; add sour cream and butter.
Beat until fluffy.
By hand, fold in spinach. Place in well-buttered baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: aunt julie's cheese pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and beat well.
Place in an 11 x 9-inch pan that has been greased well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with cinnamon or canned fruit.

title: beef teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Spread crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: low-fat minestrone soup
directions: Cook beef; drain off fat (I rinse mine).
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer an hour or longer.
This makes the large crock-pot full and is very good.

title: cherry bars
directions: Mix together like pie crust. Press on bottom of 9 X 9 pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole(make ahead the night before!)
directions: Mix eggs, dry mustard, salt and milk.
Spray Pam or lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put bread on bottom.
Place cheese on top of bread.
Place browned sausage on top of cheese.
Pour milk and egg mixture over all.
Optional: Sprinkle can of mushrooms on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry-pineapple salad
directions: In a bowl,
dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Break up cranberry sauce
and
stir	into
jello. Add pineapple, orange juice and lemon
juice.
Chill
until
partially
set. Stir in nuts. Pour into an	11
x
7 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares. Serve on lettuce leaf.
Yields 12 servings.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs and milk together. Add flour, baking powder and salt. Whip until batter is smooth. Pour batter into a squeeze bottle. Squeeze batter back and forth and around in very hot oil. Cook 1 minute on each side or until brown.
Put cake on platter and sprinkle powdered sugar or cinnamon on top. Makes 4 (6-inch) cakes.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt butter and seasoning mix together.
Add bread crumbs and mix.
Save 1/2 cup crumb mixture for the top.
Mix soup, sour cream, broccoli and crumb mixture together.
Put in casserole dish and top with cheese and crumb mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: penuche candy
directions: In saucepan, combine sugars and sour cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugars dissolved.
Cook to 240° on candy thermometer or until soft ball forms.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until mixture begins to coat nuts. Quickly turn onto wax paper.
With 2 forks, separate nuts.
Cool.

title: fruit 'n creme supreme
directions: Thoroughly mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla flavoring.
Set aside while you dice fruit. Alternate apples, bananas and nuts with sauce mix.
Top with fresh sliced strawberries.
Chill for a few hours.

title: fried beans
directions: Cut up the bacon strips in small pieces, then put them in a heavy skillet and put the broken up beans on top to fill the skillet.
Put the lid on and cook them at 325°, stirring quite often.
When they begin to stick to bottom of skillet, add water (a cup or so), then let them steam, stirring them and adding more water as needed so they won't stick.
Will take about 1 hour.

title: chinese chicken microwave
directions: Cook chicken in microwave for 10 minutes on High; cool and cut into bite sized pieces.
Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole; cook on High for 8 minutes, covered.
Let stand 3 minutes and serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Cool potatoes and eggs.
Add all ingredients and stir well. Add more mayonnaise if too dry.
Let stand in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.
If desired, sprinkle paprika on top.

title: baked pork and beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion; add to beans.
Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple waldorf
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine pineapple with apples, walnuts and celery.
Combine remaining ingredients to make a dressing and stir into pineapple mixture.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a zip-top plastic bag.
Seal bag.
Shake until meat is coated.
Remove meat from bag.
Reserve remaining flour mixture.
Brown meat in hot oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Add onion and garlic. Cook, stirring constantly, until onion is tender.
Add remaining flour mixture, green bell pepper and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender, stirring often.
Uncover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.
Serve over noodles with a dollop of sour cream and sprinkle of paprika.
Makes 6 servings.

title: weight watchers chili
directions: Broil beef. Remove to heavy cast-iron skillet on top of stove. Add remaining ingredients. Cook to desired consistency. Chopped peppers may be added. Serves 1.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Stir together brownie mix (dry), flour, oil, water and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by large tablespoons or 1/4 cupfuls 3 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or just until set and tops are dry.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Yields about 15 large cookies.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift, then measure flour.
Sift again with soda and salt. Cream Crisco and sugar; add the dry ingredients alternately with hot water.
Add oatmeal.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cream cheese, horseradish, onions, Worcestershire sauce and crab meat.
Spread in a 3 cup baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits.
Enjoy!
Serves 8.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with chips.

title: chicken and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Thoroughly combine soup mix, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and ginger with water; set aside.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 large new plastic flowerpot and some silk flowers.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Divide filling and spread evenly over tortillas; roll up.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap, twisting ends.
Refrigerate several hours.
Unwrap.
Cut into slices 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.

title: meat filled mushroom caps
directions: Wash and drain mushroom caps; remove stems.
Marinate caps for 1 hour in soy sauce.
Finely chop stems and mix with remaining ingredients.
Drain caps, reserve soy sauce.
Stuff caps with meat mixture mounded high.
Brush tops with reserved soy sauce.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Defrost and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crumble and fry beef.
Mix rice and beans in bowl.
Add meat mixture and stir together.
Pour in casserole dish and cover with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of about 12 muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches) or line with paper baking cups.
Beat egg in medium bowl; stir in milk and oil.
Stir in flour and sugar all at once just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
